op\" align=\"center\" width=200|\n'''[[The Black Eyed Peas]]'''\n<BR>[[Faithless]]\n<BR>[[Aviv Geffen]]\n<BR>[[K.Bhta|Konstantinos Vita]]\n<BR>[[Transistor]]\n|valign=\"top\" align=\"center\" width=200|\n'''[[Fatboy Slim]]'''\n<BR>[[The Ting Tings]]\n<BR>[[White Lies (band)|White Lies]]\n<BR>[[Melisses]]\n|valign=\"top\" align=\"center\" width=200|\n'''[[Ska-P]]'''\n<BR>[[Massive Attack]]\n<BR>Peyoti for President\n|}\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n| colspan=\"3\" align=\"center\" | '''Vibe Stage'''\n|-\n!Friday 1 July\n!Saturday 2 July\n!Sunday 3 July\n|-\n|valign=\"top\" align=\"center\" width=200|\n|valign=\"top\" align=\"center\" width=200|\n'''[[DJ Shadow]]'''\n<BR>Garcia plays Kyuss\n<BR>Dear Darkstar\n|valign=\"top\" align=\"center\" width=200|\n'''[[Gogol Bordello]]'''\n<BR>[[Giannis Aggelakas]]\n<BR>Ska Bangies\n|}\n\n==2009 lineup==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n| colspan=\"2\" align=\"center\" | '''Terra Stage'''\n|-\n!Saturday 27 June\n!Tuesday 30 June\n|-\n|valign=\"top\" align=\"center\" width=200|\n'''[[Placebo (band)|Placebo]]'''\n<BR>[[Moby]]\n<BR>[[Gogol Bordello]]\n<BR>[[Aviv Geffen]]\n<BR>Cabaret Balcan\n|valign=\"top\" align=\"center\" width=200|\n'''[[Slipknot (band)|Slipknot]]'''\n<BR>[[Mastodon (band)|Mastodon]]\n<BR>[[Down (band)|Down]]\n<BR>[[Kylesa]]\n<BR>[[Torche (band)|Torche]]\n|}\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n| colspan=\"2\" align=\"center\" | '''Vibe Stage'''\n|-\n!Saturday 27 June\n!Tuesday 30 June\n|-\n|valign=\"top\" align=\"center\" width=200|\n'''[[Foals (band)|Foals]]'''\n<BR>[[Expatriate (band)|Expatriate]]\n<BR>Sunny Side of the Razor\n<BR>Raintear\n|valign=\"top\" align=\"center\" width=200|\n'''[[Saxon (band)|Saxon]]'''\n<BR>[[Lita Ford]]\n<BR>Eden Demise\n<BR>God.Fear.None\n|}\n\n==2008 lineup==\nMonday 31 March was the day when Didi Music-Big Star Promotion Ltd (music concert organizer), announced the names of the artists that would perform at Rockwave Festival 2008. Along with the names they introduced the changes in the festival's whole structure. \nThe festival is now divided in two stages, \"Terra\" stage and \"Vibe\" stage (that comes by the name of the event park \"TerraVibe\"). They also abolished the division of the \"Terra\" concert area into gates PL1 and PL2, lowered the high price of the tickets and retained the special area that is on the side of the field, where there is more comfort, as there are places to sit.\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n| colspan=\"3\" align=\"center\" | '''Terra Stage'''\n|-\n!Tuesday 8 July\n!Wednesday 9 July\n!Thursday 10 July\n|-\n|valign=\"top\" align=\"center\" width=200|\n'''[[The Offspring]]'''\n<BR>[[Siouxsie Sioux]]\n<BR>[[Deus (band)|Deus]]\n<BR>[[The Gossip]]\n<BR>Abbie Gale\n|valign=\"top\" align=\"center\" width=200|\n'''[[Judas Priest]]'''\n<BR>[[Within Temptation]]\n<BR>[[Cavalera Conspiracy]]\n<BR>[[Opeth]]\n<BR>[[Morbid Angel]]\n|valign=\"top\" align=\"center\" width=270|\n'''[[Manu Chao|Manu Chao & the Radio Bemba Sound System]]'''\n<BR>[[Patti Smith]]\n<BR>[[Locomondo]]\n|}\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n| colspan=\"3\" align=\"center\" | '''Vibe Stage'''\n|-\n!Tuesday 8 July\n!Wednesday 9 July\n!Thursday 10 July\n|-\n|valign=\"top\" align=\"center\" width=200|\n'''[[Marky Ramone]]'''\n<BR>[[Flogging Molly]]\n<BR>[[Personality Crisis (band)|Personality Crisis]]\n<BR>Viper Vikings\n<BR>Pshychograndmamas\n|valign=\"top\" align=\"center\" width=200|\n'''[[Carcass (band)|Carcass]]'''\n<BR>Innerwish\n<BR>Insidead\n<BR>Universe217\n|valign=\"top\" align=\"center\" width=270|\n'''Los Mujeros'''\n<BR>Rosebleed\n<BR>No Profile\n<BR>Looming Titties\n<BR>Ska Bangies\n<BR>Sober\n<BR>Musica Ficta\n|}\n\n==2007 lineup==\nWhen the band names were first announced, [[Stone Sour]] were included in the third day of the festival. Although the band cancelled a few of their dates in their European tour, [[My Dying Bride]] filled up their spot in the third day.\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n!Friday 29 June\n!Sunday 1 July\n!Tuesday 3 July\n|-\n|valign=\"top\" align=\"center\" width=200|\n'''[[Robert Plant & The Strange Sensation]]'''\n<BR>[[Chris Cornell]]\n<BR>[[Europe (band)|Europe]]\n<BR>[[Redrum (band)|Redrum]]\n|valign=\"top\" align=\"center\" width=200|\n'''[[Heaven and Hell (band)|Heaven and Hell]]'''\n<BR>[[Dream Theater]]\n<BR>[[Iced Earth]]\n<BR>[[Anathema (band)|Anathema]]\n<BR>[[Kinetic (band)|Kinetic]]\n|valign=\"top\" align=\"center\" width=200|\n'''[[Metallica]]'''\n<BR>[[Mastodon (band)|Mastodon]]\n<BR>[[My Dying Bride]]\n<BR>Dirt Spawn Disease\n|}\n\n==2006 lineup==\n[[W.A.S.P. (band)|W.A.S.P.]] were to play on the third day but did not perform due to health issues of [[Blackie Lawless]].\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n!Monday 10 July\n!Tuesday 11 July\n!Wednesday 12 July\n|-\n|valign=\"top\" align=\"center\" width=200|\n'''[[Guns N' Roses]]'''\n<BR>Star Star\n|valign=\"top\" align=\"center\" width=200|\n'''[[Franz Ferdinand (band)|Franz Ferdinand]]'''\n<BR>[[The Dandy Warhols]]\n<BR>[[Editors (band)|Editors]]\n<BR>[[Green on Red]]\n<BR>[[Mecano]]\n<BR>The Sunday Drivers\n|valign=\"top\" align=\"center\" width=200|\n'''[[Twisted Sister]]'''\n<BR>[[Celtic Frost]]\n<BR>[[Crimson Glory]]\n<BR>[[Moonspell]]\n|}\n\n==2005 lineup==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n!Friday 24 June\n!Saturday 25 June\n!Sunday 26 June\n!Friday 8 July\n!Saturday 9 July\n|-\n|valign=\"top\" align=\"center\" width=200|\n'''[[Marilyn Manson]]'''\n<BR>[[Garbage (band)|Garbage]]\n<BR>[[Matisse (band)|Matisse]]\n|valign=\"top\" align=\"center\" width=200|\n'''[[Black Sabbath]]'''\n<BR>[[Velvet Revolver]]\n<BR>[[Black Label Society]]\n<BR>[[Wastefall]]\n|valign=\"top\" align=\"center\" width=200|\n'''[[Moby]]'''\n<BR>[[Sonic Youth]]\n<BR>[[Secret Machines]]\n<BR>[[British Sea Power]]\n<BR>Sigmatropic\n|valign=\"top\" align=\"center\" width=200|\n'''[[Slayer]]'''\n<BR>[[Accept (band)|Accept]]\n<BR>[[Candlemass (band)|Candlemass]]\n<BR>[[Dismember (band)|Dismember]]\n<BR>Order of the Ebon Hand\n|valign=\"top\" align=\"center\" width=200|\n'''[[Twisted Sister]]'''\n<BR>[[Dio (band)|Dio]]\n<BR>[[Anthrax (American band)|Anthrax]]\n<BR>[[Katatonia]]\n<BR>Olethrio Rigma\n|}\n\n==2004 lineup==\n[[Running Wild (band)|Running Wild]] did not perform and were replaced by [[Gamma Ray (band)|Gamma Ray]]. [[Muse_(band)|Muse]] were also to perform on the fourth day of the festival but cancelled and were replaced by [[Mogwai]].\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n!Friday 18 June\n!Saturday 19 June\n!Sunday 20 June\n!Monday 21 June\n!Tuesday 22 June\n|-\n|valign=\"top\" align=\"center\" width=200|\n'''[[Peter Gabriel]]'''\n<BR>Estoudiantina Neas Ionias \n|valign=\"top\" align=\"center\" width=200|\n'''[[W.A.S.P. (band)|W.A.S.P.]]'''\n<BR>[[Gamma Ray (band)|Gamma Ray]]\n<BR>[[Soulfly]]\n<BR>[[Dark Tranquility]]\n<BR>[[Firewind]]\n|valign=\"top\" align=\"center\" width=200|\n'''[[Judas Priest]]'''\n<BR>[[Nightwish]]\n<BR>[[Queensr\u00ffche]]\n<BR>[[Nightfall (band)|Nightfall]]\n|valign=\"top\" align=\"center\" width=200|\n'''[[Pixies (band)|Pixies]]'''\n<BR>[[Mogwai]]\n<BR>[[Black Rebel Motorcycle Club]]\n<BR>[[Ill Ni\u00f1o]]\n<BR>[[Raining Pleasure]] \n|valign=\"top\" align=\"center\" width=200|\n'''[[Placebo (band)|Placebo]]'''\n<BR>[[HIM (Finnish band)|HIM]]\n<BR>[[Starsailor (band)|Starsailor]]\n<BR>[[The Soundtrack of Our Lives]]\n<BR>Film\n|}\n\n==2001 lineup==\nThe festival took place in the Athens Olympic Velodrome ([[Athens Olympic Sports Complex]]) from 1 to 3 July.\n<BR>The second day of the festival was cancelled by the Greek authorities, due to reasons of safety.\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n!Sunday 1 July\n!Tuesday 3 July\n|-\n|valign=\"top\" align=\"center\" width=200|\n'''[[Judas Priest]]'''\n<BR>[[Megadeth]]\n<BR>[[Cradle of Filth]]\n<BR>[[Savatage]]\n<BR>[[Rotting Christ]]\n<BR>Less Than Human\n|valign=\"top\" align=\"center\" width=200|\n'''[[Placebo (band)|Placebo]]'''\n<BR>[[PJ Harvey]]\n<BR>[[Grandaddy]]\n<BR>[[JJ72]]\n<BR>[[Ash (band)|Ash]]\n|}\n\n==2000 lineup==\nThe festival took place in Tritsis Park in Ilion, [[Athens]].\n<BR>[[Iron Maiden]] cancelled their show at the third day, due to [[Janick Gers]]' accident at a previous show. <BR>[[The Flaming Lips]] also cancelled their show on the first day.\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n!Wednesday 12 July\n!Thursday 13 July\n!Friday 14 July\n|-\n|valign=\"top\" align=\"center\" width=200|\n'''[[Oasis (band)|Oasis]]'''\n<BR>[[Moby]]\n<BR>[[Muse (band)|Muse]]\n<BR>Closer\n|valign=\"top\" align=\"center\" width=200|\n'''[[Trypes]]'''\n<BR>[[Supergrass]]\n<BR>[[Apollo 440]]\n<BR>[[Gomez (band)|Gomez]]\n<BR>Gallon Drunk\n|valign=\"top\" align=\"center\" width=200|\n'''[[Dream Theater]]'''\n<BR>[[In Flames]]\n<BR>[[Septic Flesh]]\n<BR>On Thorns I Lay\n|}\n\n==1999 lineup==\nThe festival took place in Agios Kosmas, [[Athens]].\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n!Monday 12 July\n!Tuesday 13 July\n!Wednesday 14 July\n!Thursday 15 July\n|-\n|valign=\"top\" align=\"center\" width=200|\n'''[[Manowar]]'''\n<BR>[[Mercyful Fate]]\n<BR>[[Sodom (band)|Sodom]]\n<BR>[[Immortal (band)|Immortal]]\n<BR>[[Nightfall (band)|Nightfall]]\n<BR>Exhumation\n<BR>Horrified\n|valign=\"top\" align=\"center\" width=200|\n'''[[Blur (band)|Blur]]'''\n<BR>[[Placebo (band)|Placebo]]\n<BR>[[dEUS (band)|Deus]]\n<BR>[[Mercury Rev]]\n<BR>Purple Overdose\n<BR>Oneiropagida\n<BR>Michalis Delta\n|valign=\"top\" align=\"center\" width=200|\n'''[[Garbage (band)|Garbage]]'''\n<BR>[[Patti Smith]]\n<BR>[[Fun Lovin' Criminals]]\n<BR>Terrorvision\n<BR>Bokomolech\n<BR>Make Believe\n<BR>Closer\n|valign=\"top\" align=\"center\" width=200|\n'''[[The Prodigy]] + Terror X Crew'''\n<BR>[[The Afghan Whigs]]\n<BR>[[Bloodhound Gang]]\n<BR>[[Queens of the Stone Age]]\n<BR>The Earthbound\n<BR>Sigmatropic\n|}\n\n==1998 lineup==\nThe festival took place in Freattyda, [[Piraeus]].\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n!Monday 13 July\n!Tuesday 14 July\n!Wednesday 15 July\n!Thursday 16 July\n|-\n|valign=\"top\" align=\"center\" width=200|\n'''[[Pyx Lax]]'''\n<BR>[[Natacha Atlas]]\n<BR>[[Ypogeia Revmata]]\n<BR>Theodosia Tsatsou\n<BR>George Dimitriadis & Oi Mikroi Iroes\n<BR>Petros Theotokatos\n<BR>Valia Kalda\n|valign=\"top\" align=\"center\" width=200|\n'''[[Nick Cave and the Bad Seeds]]'''\n<BR>[[Trypes]]\n<BR>[[Moby]]\n<BR>Cornershop\n<BR>Endelechia\n<BR>Ellinistan\n|valign=\"top\" align=\"center\" width=200|\n'''[[Portishead (band)|Portishead]]'''\n<BR>[[Spiritualized]]\n<BR>[[Asian Dub Foundation]]\n<BR>[[Konstantinos Vita]]\n<BR>[[Active Member]]\n<BR>Psofioi Korioi\n|valign=\"top\" align=\"center\" width=200|\n'''[[Pulp (band)|Pulp]]'''\n<BR>[[Sonic Youth]]\n<BR>[[Xylina Spathia]]\n<BR>[[Puressence]]\n<BR>Bokomolech\n<BR>Closer\n|}\n\n==1997 lineup==\nThe festival took place in Rizoupoli Stadium, now called [[Georgios Kamaras Stadium]].\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n!Wednesday 9 July\n!Thursday 10 July\n!Friday 11 July\n|-\n|valign=\"top\" align=\"center\" width=200|\n'''Xaris & Panos Katsimichas'''\n<BR>[[Pyx Lax]]\n<BR>Sotiria Leonardou\n<BR>Ypogeia Revmata\n<BR>Manolis Famelos kai oi Podilates\n<BR>\u03a4sopana Rave\n|valign=\"top\" align=\"center\" width=200|\n'''[[The Sisters of Mercy]]'''\n<BR>[[New Model Army (band)|New Model Army]]\n<BR>[[Diafana Krina]]\n<BR>Flowers of Romance\n<BR>Love in Sadness\n|valign=\"top\" align=\"center\" width=200|\n'''[[Megadeth]]'''\n<BR>[[Bruce Dickinson]] feat. [[Adrian Smith]]\n<BR>[[Grip Inc.]]\n<BR>[[Rotting Christ]]\n<BR>Dark Nova\n|}\n\n==1996 lineup==\nThe first festival was called \"Rock of Gods\" and took place in the Dock 3 of the Piraeus harbour. \n<BR>[[Mot\u00f6rhead]] was included in the first day of the festival, but cancelled and [[Saxon (band)|Saxon]] filled up their spot. [[Foo Fighters]] were to play on the third day of the festival, but [[Dave Grohl]] broke his arm at a previous show and [[Violent Femmes]] took their place.\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n!Friday 12 July\n!Saturday 13 July\n!Sunday 14 July\n|-\n|valign=\"top\" align=\"center\" width=200|\n'''[[Slayer]]'''\n<BR>[[Saxon (band)|Saxon]]\n<BR>[[Blind Guardian]]\n<BR>[[Rage (German band)|Rage]]\n<BR>[[Nightfall (band)|Nightfall]]\n<BR>Fatal Morgana\n|valign=\"top\" align=\"center\" width=200|\n'''[[Violent Femmes]]'''\n<BR>[[The Jesus and Mary Chain]]\n<BR>[[Bad Religion]]\n<BR>[[Paradise Lost (band)|Paradise Lost]]\n<BR>Dead Moon\n<BR>Bokomolech\n|valign=\"top\" align=\"center\" width=200|\n'''[[Iggy Pop]]'''\n<BR>[[Violent Femmes]]\n<BR>[[Moby]]\n<BR>Stereo Nova\n<BR>In Trance '95\n<BR>Oh! My Garden\n|}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.rockwavefestival.gr Rockwave Festival official Website (in Greek)]\n*[http://www.terravibe.gr/ Terra Vibe the festival hosting area]\n*[http://www.didimusic.gr/ Didi Music-Big Star Promotion Official Website (in Greek)]\n\n{{coord missing|Greece}}\n\n[[Category:Rock festivals in Greece]]\n[[Category:Heavy metal festivals]]\n[[Category:Music festivals in Greece]]\n[[Category:Music festivals established in 1996]]\n[[Category:Tourist attractions in Attica]]\n[[Category:Events in Attica]]\n[[Category:Electronic music festivals in Greece]]\n[[Category:1996 establishments in Greece]]\n[[Category:Summer events in Greece]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=May 2019}}\n{{infobox music festival\n | music_festival_name = Rockwave Festival\n | image = [[File:Rockwave2009.jpg|200px]]\n | caption = Terra Stage, Rockwave Festival, 2009\n | imagesize = 200px\n | location = [[Terra Vibe Park|TerraVibe Park]], [[Malakasa]], Greece\n | years_active= 1996\u20132001, 2004-2018, 2020-\n | dates = June\u2013July\n | genre = [[Alternative rock]], [[Rock music|rock]], [[Heavy metal music|metal]], [[Pop music|pop]]\n | website = [http://www.rockwavefestival.gr www.rockwavefestival.gr]\n}}\n\n'''Rockwave Festival''' is a [[rock festival]] that takes place  in [[Malakasa]], [[Greece]], near [[Athens]]. It is one of the most famous [[music festival]]s in Greece. The festival's history begins in 1996, but its popularity has spread since 2004. The festival's location was constantly being changed until 2004, when event park [[Terra Vibe Park|TerraVibe Park]], located in Attica, became the permanent venue of the festival.\n\n==2020 lineup==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n| colspan=\"4\" align=\"center\" | '''Terra Stage'''\n|-\n!Saturday 6 June\n!Saturday 27 June\n|-\n|valign=\"top\" align=\"center\" width=200|\n'''[[Deep Purple]]'''\n<BR>[[Opeth]]\n|valign=\"top\" align=\"center\" width=200|\n'''[[Placebo (band)|Placebo]]'''\n<BR>[[Belle and Sebastian]]\n<BR>Digital 21 + Stefan Olsdal\n|}\n\n==2018 lineup==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n| colspan=\"3\" align=\"center\" | '''Terra Stage'''\n|-\n!Friday 6 July\n!Thursday 19 July\n!Friday 20 July\n|-\n|valign=\"top\" align=\"center\" width=200|\n'''[[Arctic Monkeys]]'''\n<BR>[[alt-J]]\n<BR>[[Miles Kane]]\n<BR>[[Get Well Soon (band)|Get Well Soon]]\n<BR>Coretheband\n|valign=\"top\" align=\"center\" width=200|\n'''[[Judas Priest]]'''\n<BR>[[Saxon (band)|Saxon]]\n<BR>[[Accept (band)|Accept]]\n|valign=\"top\" align=\"center\" width=200|\n'''[[Iron Maiden]]'''\n<BR>[[Tremonti (band)|Tremonti]]\n<BR>Monument\n|}\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n| colspan=\"3\" align=\"center\" | '''Vibe Stage'''\n|-\n!Friday 6 July\n!Thursday 19 July\n!Friday 20 July\n|-\n|valign=\"top\" align=\"center\" width=200|\n|valign=\"top\" align=\"center\" width=200|\n'''[[Sabaton (band)|Sabaton]]'''\n<BR>Foray Between Ocean\n<BR>Null'O'Zero\n<BR>Jacks Full\n|valign=\"top\" align=\"center\" width=200|\n'''[[Volbeat]]'''\n<BR>[[The Raven Age]]\n<BR>W.E.B.\n<BR>Rollin' Dice\n|}\n\n==2017 lineup==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n| colspan=\"3\" align=\"center\" | '''Terra Stage'''\n|-\n!Friday 30 June\n!Saturday 1 July\n!Sunday 2 July\n|-\n|valign=\"top\" align=\"center\" width=200|\n'''[[Rotting Christ]]'''\n<BR>Nightstalker\n<BR>InnerWish\n|valign=\"top\" align=\"center\" width=200|\n'''[[Placebo (band)|Placebo]]'''\n<BR>[[Sivert Hoyem]]\n<BR>[[Fat White Family]]\n<BR>The Last International Playboys\n|valign=\"top\" align=\"center\" width=200|\n'''[[Evanescence]]'''\n<B