oricon20111219\" /><ref name=\"babyblossom\">{{cite web|url=http://www.tokyohive.com/2012/01/akb48-forms-a-band-for-give-me-five-jacket-covers/ |title=AKB48 forms a band for \"GIVE ME FIVE!\" + jacket covers |publisher=Tokyohive.com |date=January 23, 2012 |accessdate=April 25, 2013}}</ref> \"Give Me Five!\" was released on February 15.<ref name=\"oricon20111219\" />\n\nAKB48's second documentary film, ''Documentary of AKB48: Show Must Go On Sh\u014djo-tachi wa Kizutsuki Nagara, Yume wo Miru'', opened on January 27<ref name=\"eiga\">{{cite web |url= http://eiga.com/movie/57607/|title= DOCUMENTARY of AKB48 Show must go on \u5c11\u5973\u305f\u3061\u306f\u50b7\u3064\u304d\u306a\u304c\u3089\u3001\u5922\u3092\u898b\u308b|accessdate= January 27, 2014|work= eiga.com|language= Japanese}}</ref> in seventh place<ref name=\"ann20120204\">{{cite web |url= http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2012-02-04/japanese-box-office-january-28-29|title= Japanese Box Office, January 28\u201329|date= February 4, 2012|accessdate= January 27, 2014|work= [[Anime News Network]]}}</ref> at the box office and grossed nearly $4&nbsp;million by February 19.<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2012-02-28/japanese-box-office-february-18-19|title= Japanese Box Office, February 18\u201319|date= February 28, 2012|accessdate= January 27, 2014|work= [[Anime News Network]]}}</ref> An [[anime]] series, ''[[AKB0048]]'', was developed by [[Satelight]]<ref name=\"oricon20111018\">{{cite web | url = http://www.oricon.co.jp/news/movie/2002820/full/ | title = AKB48\u521d\u306eTV\u30a2\u30cb\u30e1\u5316\u6c7a\u5b9a\u3000\"\u58f0\u512a\u9078\u629c\"9\u4eba\u304c\u4e3b\u984c\u6b4c\u3082\u62c5\u5f53| publisher = Oricon, Inc | date = October 18, 2011 |language= Japanese}}</ref> and aired from April 29 to July 22. It was directed by [[Yoshimasa Hiraike]], with group producer Akimoto aiding with planning and supervision.<ref name=\"oricon20111018\" /> Nine members of AKB48 and its sister groups voiced the main characters, singing its opening and closing themes<ref name=\"ann20120201\">{{cite web | url = http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/interest/2012-02-01/akb48-akb0048-anime-cast-roles-revealed | title = AKB48's AKB0048 Anime Cast Roles Revealed | publisher = Anime News Network |accessdate=June 5, 2012 | date = February 1, 2012 |language= Japanese}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2011-11-25/akb48-akb0048-anime-gets-4-manga-series-in-4-mags |title=AKB48's AKB0048 Anime Gets 4 Manga Series in 4 Mags \u2013 News |publisher=Anime News Network |date=April 21, 2013 |accessdate=April 25, 2013}}</ref> as No Name.<ref name=\"ann20120426\">{{cite web | url = http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/interest/2012-04-26/akb0048-themes-sung-by-new-akb-related-no-name-unit | title = AKB0048's Themes Sung by AKB48 Spinoff Unit 'No Name' | publisher = Anime News Network |accessdate=June 5, 2012 | date = April 26, 2012 |language= Japanese}}</ref>\n\nAfter photographs with their boyfriends surfaced, Natsumi Hirajima and Rumi Yonezawa resigned from the group<ref name=\"natalie20120128\">{{cite web | url = http://natalie.mu/music/news/63495 | title = AKB48\u7c73\u6ca2\u7460\u7f8e\uff06\u5e73\u5d8b\u590f\u6d77\u3001\u30b0\u30eb\u30fc\u30d7\u3092\u96e2\u8131 | work = [[Natalie (website)|Natalie]] | publisher=[[Natasha, Inc.]] | date = January 28, 2012 | accessdate = March 25, 2012 |language= Japanese}}</ref><!----and made their last appearance at a handshake event on February 5.<ref name=\"natalie20120128\" />---> and were replaced by [[Jurina Matsui]] of [[SKE48]] and Miyuki Watanabe of [[NMB48]].<ref name=\"natalie20120128\" /><ref name=\"natalie201203251\" /> On March 24 AKB48 announced that five trainees would be promoted to Team 4, expanding its roster to 16.<ref name=\"natalie201203251\">{{cite web | url = http://natalie.mu/music/news/66661 | title = SKE\u677e\u4e95\u73e0\u7406\u5948\u3001NMB\u6e21\u8fba\u7f8e\u512a\u7d00\u304cAKB48\u306b\u671f\u9593\u9650\u5b9a\u52a0\u5165 | work = [[Natalie (website)|Natalie]] | publisher=[[Natasha, Inc.]] | accessdate = March 25, 2012 | date = March 25, 2012 |language= Japanese}}</ref> It was also announced that the group would perform at the [[Tokyo Dome]] stadium, one of AKB48's main goals since it was founded.<ref name=\"natalie20120524\">{{cite web | url = http://natalie.mu/music/news/69916 | title = AKB48\u3001\u521d\u306e\u6771\u4eac\u30c9\u30fc\u30e0\u30b3\u30f3\u30b5\u30fc\u30c8\u306f3DAYS\u516c\u6f14 | work = [[Natalie (website)|Natalie]] | publisher=[[Natasha, Inc.]] | date = April 24, 2012 | accessdate = June 5, 2012 |language= Japanese}}</ref><ref name=\"natalie201203252\">{{cite web | url = http://natalie.mu/music/news/66660 | title = SKE\u677e\u4e95\u73e0\u7406\u5948\u3001NMB\u6e21\u8fba\u7f8e\u512a\u7d00\u304cAKB48\u306b\u671f\u9593\u9650\u5b9a\u52a0\u5165 | work = [[Natalie (website)|Natalie]] | publisher=[[Natasha, Inc.]] | date = March 25, 2012 |accessdate=March 25, 2012 |language= Japanese}}</ref>\n\nOn March 25, longtime headliner [[Atsuko Maeda]] announced her graduation from the group.<ref name=\"mantan20120325\">{{cite web | url = http://mantan-web.jp/2012/03/25/20120325dog00m200029000c.html | title = AKB48\u524d\u7530\u6566\u5b50 \uff1a\u4e0d\u52d5\u306e\u30bb\u30f3\u30bf\u30fc\u304c\u5352\u696d\u3092\u767a\u8868\u30006\u5e74\u534a\u306e\u6d3b\u52d5\u306b\u5e55 | publisher = Mainichi Shimbun Digital Co. Ltd | date = March 25, 2012 |accessdate=March 26, 2012 |language= Japanese}}</ref> AKB48 announced that Maeda would graduate after the Tokyo Dome concerts;<ref name=\"oricon20120530\">{{cite web | url = http://www.oricon.co.jp/news/music/2012272/full/ | title = \u524d\u7530\u6566\u5b50\u3001AKB\u5352\u696d\u5f8c\u521d\u306e\u30bd\u30ed\u516c\u6f14\u6c7a\u5b9a\u30009\u6708\u306b\u6771\u4eac\uff06\u795e\u6238\u3067 |accessdate= June 5, 2012 | publisher = Oricon, Inc | date = May 30, 2012 |language= Japanese}}</ref> her final performance (and graduation ceremony) took place in the AKB48 theater on August 27,<ref name=\"oricon2026059\">{{cite web | url = http://www.oricon.co.jp/news/entertainment/2026059/full/ | script-title=ja:\u677f\u91ce\u53cb\u7f8e\u3001\u6566\u5b50\u3068\u306e\"\u518d\u4f1a\"\u300c\u3046\u308c\u3057\u3044\u300d |accessdate= July 4, 2013 | publisher = Oricon, Inc | date = June 28, 2012 |language= Japanese}}</ref> and was streamed live on YouTube.<ref name=\"oricon2015882\">{{cite web | url = http://www.oricon.co.jp/news/music/2015882/full/ | title = AKB\u524d\u7530\u5352\u696d\u516c\u6f14\u3092Google\uff0b\uff06YouTube\u3067\u5b8c\u5168\u751f\u914d\u4fe1\u3000\u30d5\u30a1\u30f3\u306e\u6295\u7a3f\u304c\u516c\u6f14\u306e\u6f14\u51fa\u306b\uff01 |accessdate= July 4, 2013 | publisher = Oricon, Inc | date = August 21, 2012 |language= Japanese}}</ref>\n\nOn March 26 AKB48 announced an election for the lineup for the group's 27th major-label single, \"[[Gingham Check]]\". The candidates were 243 members of AKB48, SKE48, NMB48 and HKT48,<ref name=\"oricon20120326\">{{cite web | url = http://www.oricon.co.jp/news/entertainment/2009106/full/ | title = AKB\u3001\u4eca\u5e74\u30826\u6708\u306b\u7dcf\u9078\u6319\u3000\u904e\u53bb\u6700\u591a240\u4eba\u8d85\u51fa\u99ac\u3000\u524d\u7530\u306e\u53c2\u52a0\u306f\uff1f | work = [[Natalie (website)|Natalie]] | publisher=[[Natasha, Inc.]] | date = March 26, 2012 |accessdate=March 26, 2012 |language= Japanese}}</ref> and ballots were included with the group's 26th single (\"[[Manatsu no Sounds Good!]]\").<ref name=\"japantoday20120607\"/> The election was held June 6 at [[Nippon Budokan]], with the results telecast live.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.japantimes.co.jp/text/fm20120531a1.html|title=AKB48 'election' shows marketing brilliance|date=May 31, 2012|accessdate=July 21, 2012|author=Patrick St. Michel and Daisuke Kikuchi|publisher=[[Japan Times]]}}</ref> [[Yuko Oshima]] finished first, followed by [[Mayu Watanabe]] and [[Yuki Kashiwagi]].<ref name=\"japantoday20120607\">{{cite web|url=http://www.japantoday.com/category/entertainment/view/oshima-voted-akb48s-most-popular-singer |archive-url=https://archive.today/20121123180609/http://www.japantoday.com/category/entertainment/view/oshima-voted-akb48s-most-popular-singer |url-status = dead|archive-date=November 23, 2012 |title=Oshima's win in AKB48 election big news in Japan |first=Harumi |last=Ozawa |publisher=Japan Today |date=June 7, 2012 |accessdate=July 21, 2012 }}</ref>\n\nOn April 23 AKB48 announced the creation of its third overseas sister group, [[SNH48]], based in Shanghai.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.asahi.com/showbiz/nikkan/NIK201204230003.html|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120423174840/http://www.asahi.com/showbiz/nikkan/NIK201204230003.html|script-title=ja:\uff21\uff2b\uff2248\u30b0\u30eb\u30fc\u30d7\u4eca\u5ea6\u306f\u4e0a\u6d77|archivedate=April 23, 2012|accessdate=November 5, 2015|publisher=Asahi Shimbun|language=Japanese}}</ref> It was announced on June 17 that [[Rino Sashihara]] would be transferred to [[HKT48]] in July as a \"restart\" because of an alleged scandal involving her ex-boyfriend.<ref name=\"oricon20120617\">{{cite web |url=http://www.oricon.co.jp/news/entertainment/2013090/full/?cat_id=tw |title=\u3055\u3057\u3053\u3001AKB48\u30c1\u30fc\u30e0A\u6700\u7d42\u516c\u6f14\u306f6\u30fb20 |date=June 17, 2012 |accessdate=June 24, 2012|language=Japanese}}</ref> On June 24 AKB48 announced the promotion of six trainees from the 10th and 11th generations<ref name=\"natalie20120624\" /> and its third rock-paper-scissors tournament (scheduled for September 18) to determine the lineup for the group's 29th single, \"[[Eien Pressure]]\".<ref name=\"natalie20120624\">{{cite web |url=http://natalie.mu/music/news/71685 |title=AKB48\u30a2\u30eb\u30d0\u30e0\u3092\u30c9\u30fc\u30e0\u524d\u767a\u58f2\uff06\u3058\u3083\u3093\u3051\u3093\u5927\u4f1a\u958b\u50ac\u6c7a\u5b9a |date=June 24, 2012 |accessdate=June 24, 2012|language=Japanese}}</ref>\n\nOn August 15 the group released its fourth album, ''[[1830m]]'', and on August 24 (the first day of its Tokyo Dome concert series) AKB48 announced a reorganization of its teams. Team 4 was dissolved, with its members transferred to the other three teams. Aika \u014cta was transferred to [[HKT48]], [[Aki Takaj\u014d]] and Haruka Nakagawa to Jakarta-based [[JKT48]] and [[Sae Miyazawa]] and [[Mariya Suzuki]] to SNH48.<ref>{{cite web|first=Tommy | last = Kono |url=http://www.akb48wrapup.com/2013/02/in-shanghai-miyazawa-sae-struggling-to-lead-an-immature-snh48-members/ |title=In Shanghai, Miyazawa Sae struggling to lead immature SNH48 members \u2022 AKB48WrapUp |publisher=Akb48wrapup.com |date=February 21, 2013 |accessdate=September 25, 2013}}</ref> [[Minami Takahashi]] became general manager of AKB48, with [[Mariko Shinoda]] replacing her as Team A captain. [[Yuko Oshima]] became Team K captain, and [[Ayaka Umeda]] captain of Team B.<ref name=\"AKB48 Official Blog\">{{cite web |url=http://www.akb48.co.jp/news/detail.php?id=7929 |title= Reformation of AKB48 in Tokyo Dome Concert |date=August 24, 2012 |language=Japanese}}</ref><ref name=\"crunchyroll_20120824\">{{cite web|url=http://www.crunchyroll.com/anime-news/2012/08/24/akb48-announces-tectonic-line-up-shift|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120910054320/http://www.crunchyroll.com/anime-news/2012/08/24/akb48-announces-tectonic-line-up-shift|title=AKB48 Announces Tectonic Line-Up Shift|archivedate=September 10, 2012|accessdate=November 5, 2015|work=Crunchyroll}}</ref>\n\n=== 2012\u20132014: ''Tsugi no Ashiato'' ===\n[[File:AKB\u304c\u5927\u718a\u306e\u5c0f\u5b66\u6821\u306b\u6765\u305f \u604b\u3059\u308b\u30d5\u30a9\u30fc\u30c1\u30e5\u30f3\u30af\u30c3\u30ad\u30fc (2).jpg|thumb|upright=1.2|AKB48 in Tokyo in 2013]]\nAKB48 recorded \"[[Sugar Rush (AKB48 song)|Sugar Rush]]\" for the 2012 Disney animated film, ''[[Wreck-It Ralph]]'',<ref>{{cite news|title=Walt Disney Animation Studios' \"Wreck-It Ralph\" Scores Big with Composer Henry Jackman, Plus Original Music from Skrillex, AKB48, Owl City and Buckner & Garcia|url=http://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/walt-disney-animation-studios-wreck-it-ralph-scores-big-with-composer-henry-jackman-plus-original-music-from-skrillex-akb48-owl-city-and-buckner--garcia-169663046.html|accessdate=September 29, 2012|newspaper=PR Newswire|date=September 13, 2012|author=Walt Disney Records}}</ref> and the group set a Guinness World Record for the most pop singers in a video game (its [[dating simulation game]], ''AKB1/149 Ren'ai S\u014dsenkyo'').<ref name=\"sanspo20121207\">{{cite web|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121210161301/http://www.sanspo.com/geino/news/20121207/akb12120705030001-n1.html |archivedate=December 10, 2012 |url=http://www.sanspo.com/geino/news/20121207/akb12120705030001-n1.html |script-title=ja:\u30ae\u30cd\u30b9\u8a8d\u5b9a\u306b\u307e\u3086\u3086\u300c\u4e16\u754c\u306b\u7fbd\u3070\u305f\u304f\u4e00\u6b69\u300d |date=December 7, 2012 |language=Japanese |url-status = dead|df=mdy }}</ref> It won a second consecutive [[Japan Record Award]], for \"[[Manatsu no Sounds Good!]]\". The group was the number one artist by total sales revenue in Japan in 2012, with \u00a519.098 billion.<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.tokyohive.com/article/2012/12/oricon-reveals-artist-total-sales-revenue-ranking-for-2012/|title= Oricon reveals \"Artist Total Sales Revenue\" ranking for 2012|date= December 20, 2012|accessdate= April 22, 2015|work= tokyohive|publisher= 6Theory Media, LLC}}</ref> The ''[[AKB0048]]'' anime series was renewed for a second season, ''AKB0048 Next Stage'', and aired from January 5 to March 30, 2013. In January 2013 AKB48 played its Request Hour Set List Best 100 concert at [[Tokyo Dome City Hall]], announcing future shows at [[Nippon Budokan]]<ref>{{cite news|title=AKB48 and sister groups to hold live concerts at Nippon Budokan in April|url=http://www.tokyohive.com/2013/01/akb48-and-sister-groups-to-hold-live-concerts-at-nippon-budokan-in-april/|accessdate=January 28, 2013|date=January 26, 2013|work=Tokyohive}}</ref> and [[Nissan Stadium]] (the first show by a female artist at the latter).<ref>{{cite news|title=AKB48 to hold an open-air live concert \"AKB48 Super Festival\" at Nissan Stadium|url=http://www.tokyohive.com/2013/01/akb48-to-hold-an-open-air-live-concert-akb48-super-festival-at-nissan-stadium/|accessdate=January 28, 2013|date=January 27, 2013|work=Tokyohive}}</ref> On February 1, the film ''Documentary of AKB48: No Flower Without Rain: Sh\u014djo Tachi wa Namida no Ato ni Nani o Miru?''.<ref name=\"eiga2\">{{cite web |url= http://eiga.com/movie/77715/|title= DOCUMENTARY of AKB48 No flower without rain \u5c11\u5973\u305f\u3061\u306f\u6d99\u306e\u5f8c\u306b\u4f55\u3092\u898b\u308b\uff1f|accessdate= January 27, 2014|work= eiga.com|language= Japanese}}</ref> opened in tenth place at the box office,<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2013-02-10/japanese-box-office-february-2-3|title= Japanese Box Office, February 2\u20133|date= February 10, 2013|accessdate= January 27, 2014|work= [[Anime News Network]]}}</ref> and grossed $2.2&nbsp;million by February 17.<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2013-02-24/japanese-box-office-february-16-17|title= Japanese Box Office, February 16\u201317 (Updated)|date= February 24, 2013|accessdate= January 27, 2014|work= [[Anime News Network]]}}</ref> During a meet-and-greet event for the film, first-generation member [[Tomomi Itano]] announced that she was leaving the group.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.tokyohive.com/2013/02/itano-tomomi-to-graduate-from-akb48-this-year/ |title=Itano Tomomi to graduate from AKB48 this year |work=Tokyohive |accessdate=February 2, 2013}}</ref> On April 28, after a <!--- AKB48 Group Rinji Soukai{{not in source given|date=June 2013}} --->Nippon Budokan concert, AKB48's general manager announced another reorganization of the teams (including the girls who were also members of its sister groups).<ref>{{cite web|last=Kono |first=Tommy |url=http://www.akb48wrapup.com/2013/04/akb48-announced-5-dome-tour-in-2013-summer-and-team-shuffle-at-budokan-concert-final/ |title=AKB48 announced 5-Dome Tour in 2013 Summer and Team Shuffle at Budokan Concert Final |work=AKB48WrapUp.com |date=October 24, 2012 |accessdate=April 29, 2013}}</ref> Nito Moeno and [[Tomomi Kasai]] also made their final appearances with the group.{{failed verification|date=June 2013|reason=article does not say they were graduating or what}}\n\nAKB48 released its 31st single, \"[[Sayonara Crawl]]\" (an election single), on May 22.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://natalie.mu/music/news/87448|title=AKB48\u3001\u4eca\u5e74\u306e\u7dcf\u9078\u6319\u306f\u7acb\u5019\u88dc\u5236\uff06\u65e5\u7523\u30b9\u30bf\u30b8\u30a2\u30e0\u3067\u958b\u7968|publisher=[[Natalie (website)|Natalie]]|date=March 27, 2013|accessdate=April 17, 2013|language=Japanese}}</ref> It sold more than 1.9&nbsp;million copies in its first month,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://aramatheydidnt.livejournal.com/4883811.html?thread=245931619 |archive-url=https://archive.today/20130617230823/http://aramatheydidnt.livejournal.com/4883811.html?thread=245931619 |url-status = dead|archive-date=June 17, 2013 |title=Weekly Oricon Chart: Albums/Singles/Music-DVDs |publisher=aramatheydidnt |date=June 16, 2013 |accessdate=June 18, 2013 }}</ref> breaking [[Speed (Japanese band)|Speed]]'s ''White Love'' 1997 record for the highest single sales by a female group.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.tnsori.com/archives/51967089.html|title=AKB48\u300c\u3055\u3088\u306a\u3089\u30af\u30ed\u30fc\u30eb\u300d\u7d2f\u7a4d\u58f2\u4e0a185\u4e07\u679a\u7a81\u7834\u3001SPEED\u300cWhite Love\u300d\u3092\u4e0a\u56de\u308a\u5973\u6027\u30b0\u30eb\u30fc\u30d7\u53f2\u4e0a\u6700\u9ad8\u8a18\u9332\u66f4\u65b0\uff01|publisher=The Natsu Style|language=Japanese|date=June 3, 2013}}</ref> The election candidates were 246 girls from AKB48, its sister groups and former members.<ref name=\"tokyohiveresults2013\"/> On June 8 the results were broadcast on [[Fuji Television|Fuji TV]] and streamed live on YouTube, the latter with Japanese and English commentary.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://j-entonline.com/asian-entertainment/japanese-entertainment-news/akb48-general-elections-june-8-2013-j-ent-coverage-begins-at-100-a-m-pst/ |title=AKB48 General Elections (June 8, 2013) J!-ENT Coverage for AKB48 32nd Single Senbatsu Sosenkyou \u2013 1:00 a.m. \u2013 2:00 PST (5:00\u20136:00 PM \u2013 Tokyo) |date=June 7, 2013 |work=J-Ent! Online |url-status = dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131005041809/http://j-entonline.com/asian-entertainment/japanese-entertainment-news/akb48-general-elections-june-8-2013-j-ent-coverage-begins-at-100-a-m-pst/ |archivedate=October 5, 2013 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://j-entonline.com/asian-entertainment/japanese-entertainment-news/akb48-general-elections-june-8-2013-j-ent-coverage-for-akb48-32nd-single-senbatsu-sosenkyou-post-election-coverage/ |title=AKB48 General Elections (June 8, 2013) \u2013 J!-ENT Post Election Coverage for the AKB48 32nd Single Senbatsu Sosenkyou \u2013 Interview with Melody Dassance |date=June 8, 2013 |last=Amith |first=Dennis |work=J-Ent! Online |url-status = dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131005041930/http://j-entonline.com/asian-entertainment/japanese-entertainment-news/akb48-general-elections-june-8-2013-j-ent-coverage-for-akb48-32nd-single-senbatsu-sosenkyou-post-election-coverage/ |archivedate=October 5, 2013 }}</ref> The winner was [[HKT48]] member [[Rino Sashihara]], a former member of AKB48.<ref name=\"tokyohiveresults2013\">{{cite web|title=[Completed] AKB48 32nd Single Senbatsu General Election results!|url=http://www.tokyohive.com/article/2013/06/akb48-32nd-single-senbatsu-general-election-results|work=8 June 2013|publisher=Tokyohive|accessdate=June 11, 2013}}</ref><ref name=\"election2013\">{{cite web|url=http://www.akb48.co.jp/sousenkyo/32ndsingle/result.php|title = AKB48 32nd\u30b7\u30f3\u30b0\u30eb \u9078\u629c\u7dcf\u9078\u6319 |trans-title=32nd single selection elections | work = AKB48 Official Site | date = June 8, 2013 | language=Japanese}}</ref> During the event, Team A captain [[Mariko Shinoda]] (who placed fifth) announced that she would leave the group in July.<ref>{{cite web|title=AKB48's Shinoda Mariko announces her graduation from the group next month|url=http://www.tokyohive.com/article/2013/06/akb48s-shinoda-mariko-announces-her-graduation-from-the-group-next-month|work=8 June 2013|publisher=Tokyohive|accessdate=June 11, 2013}}</ref> On July 31, during AKB48's summer concert series at the Sapporo Dome, guest and former group headliner [[Atsuko Maeda]] sang her new solo single (\"[[Time Machine Nante Iranai]]\").<ref>{{cite web|url= http://www.japantoday.com/category/entertainment/view/atsuko-maeda-makes-guest-appearance-at-akb48-concert|title= Atsuko Maeda makes guest appearance at AKB48 concert |date=July 31, 2013|accessdate= August 24, 2013|work= Japan Today}}</ref>\n\nOn August 21 the group released its 32nd single, \"[[Koisuru Fortune Cookie]]\". Its music video had 3,800 extras,<ref name=\"Yomiuri_20130624\">{{cite web|url=http://hochi.yomiuri.co.jp/entertainment/news/20130624-OHT1T00024.htm|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130624074856/http://hochi.yomiuri.co.jp/entertainment/news/20130624-OHT1T00024.htm|script-title=ja:\uff13\uff18\uff10\uff10\u4eba\u80cc\u306b\u30bb\u30f3\u30bf\u30fc\u3055\u3057\u3053\uff01\uff21\uff2b\uff22\u65b0\u66f2\u300c\u604b\u3059\u308b\u30d5\u30a9\u30fc\u30c1\u30e5\u30f3\u30af\u30c3\u30ad\u30fc\u300d|archivedate=June 24, 2013|accessdate=November 5, 2015|publisher=The Hochi Simbum|language=Japanese}}</ref> the most for any AKB48- and sister group-related video.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://natalie.mu/music/pp/ske4804 | language=Japanese | title=<nowiki>[Power Push]</nowiki> SKE48 (1/3) |work=[[Natalie (website)|Natalie Music News]] |date=August 1, 2011|accessdate=June 29, 2013}}</ref> On August 24 the group announced the restoration of Team 4, with [[Minami Minegishi]] as captain and members promoted from the 13th and 14th generation of trainees.<ref name=\"melos20130824\">{{cite web | url = http://melosnomichi.blogspot.com/2013/08/akb48-new-minegishi-team-4-created.html | title = AKB48 New (Minegishi) Team 4 Created | work = Melos no Michi |date = August 24, 2013}}</ref>\n\nOn September 18, AKB48 held its annual rock-paper-scissors tournament at Nippon Budokan to determine the lineup for its 34th single,<ref>{{cite web|title=AKB48 Holds Their 34th Single Senbatsu Janken Tournament at Nippon Budokan|url=http://www.jpopasia.com/news/akb48-holds-their-34th-single-senbatsu-janken-tournament-at-nippon-budokan::14311.html|date=June 23, 2013|work=Jpopasia}}</ref> with [[Jurina Matsui]] the winner.<ref name=\"rpsresults2013\">{{cite web | url = http://nihongogo.com/2013/09/jurina-matsui-wins-jankenpyon-tournament-to-lead-akb48s-34th-single/ | title = Jurina Matsui Wins Jankenpyon Tournament to Lead AKB48\u2032s 34th Single | work = Nihongogo | first = Jeremy | last = Suskin | date = September 18, 2013}}</ref> After the event the group announced the lineup and performed its 33rd single, \"[[Heart Electric]]\", which was released in October.<ref name=\"single33lineup\">{{cite web | url = http://allthingsjpop.wordpress.com/2013/09/19/first-performance-of-akb48-33rd-single-heart-electric/ | title = First performance of AKB48 33rd Single | work = allthingsjpop.wordpress.com | date = September 19, 2013 }}</ref> Its music video was directed by [[Shusuke Kaneko]], known for the Heisei [[Gamera]] trilogy ''[[Godzilla, Mothra and King Ghidorah: Giant Monsters All-Out Attack]]'' and the live-action film version of ''[[Death Note (2006 film)|Death Note]]''.<ref name=\"natalie20131005\">{{cite web|url=http://natalie.mu/music/news/100824 |title=\u30ca\u30bf\u30ea\u30fc \u2013 AKB48\u300c\u30cf\u30fc\u30c8\u30fb\u30a8\u30ec\u30ad\u300d1960\u5e74\u4ee3\u98a8\u30b8\u30e3\u30b1\uff06PV\u5b8c\u6210 |language = Japanese | publisher=[[Natalie.mu]] |date=October 5, 2013 |accessdate=October 7, 2013}}</ref> On December 11 the group released its 34th single, \"[[Suzukake no Ki no Michi de \"Kimi no Hohoemi o Yume ni Miru\" to Itte Shimattara Bokutachi no Kankei wa D\u014d Kawatte Shimau no ka, Bokunari ni Nan-nichi ka Kangaeta Ue de no Yaya Kihazukashii Ketsuron no Y\u014d na Mono|Suzukake no Ki no Michi de 'Kimi no Hohoemi o Yume ni Miru' to Itte Shimattara Bokutachi no Kankei wa D\u014d Kawatte Shimau no ka, Bokunari ni Nan-nichi ka Kangaeta Ue de no Yaya Kihazukashii Ketsuron no Y\u014d na Mono]]\",<ref>{{cite news|date=November 6, 2013|url=http://www.oricon.co.jp/news/music/2030508/full/|title=AKB\u53f2\u4e0a\u6700\u9577\uff01\u3000\u73e0\u7406\u5948\u30bb\u30f3\u30bf\u30fc\u65b0\u66f2\u306f76\u5b57\u3000\u4f5c\u66f2\u306f\u7e54\u7530\u54f2\u90ce\u304c\u62c5\u5f53|publisher=ORICON STYLE|language=Japanese|accessdate=November 6, 2013}}</ref> and on December 31 longtime member [[Yuko Oshima]] announced on ''[[K\u014dhaku Uta Gassen]]'' that she was leaving the group.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2013-12-31/idol-yuko-oshima-graduates-from-akb48 |title=Idol Yuko Oshima Announces Plans to Graduate From AKB48 \u2013 News |publisher=Anime News Network |date=December 31, 2013 |accessdate=January 1, 2014}}</ref> The group was the 2nd artist by total sales revenue in Japan in 2013, with \u00a513.254 billion.<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.tokyohive.com/article/2013/12/oricon-2013-yearly-charts-artist-total-sales|title= Oricon 2013 Yearly Charts : Artist Total Sales|date= December 16, 2013|accessdate= April 22, 2015|work= tokyohive|publisher= 6Theory Media, LLC}}</ref>\n\nOn January 22, 2014, AKB48 released the album ''[[Tsugi no Ashiato]]''. It reached number one on the weekly [[Oricon Albums Chart]], selling 962,000 copies.<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.tokyohive.com/article/2014/01/akb48s-latest-album-sells-over-950000-copies-in-the-first-week|title= AKB48's latest album sells over 950,000 copies in the first week|date= January 27, 2014|accessdate= January 27, 2014|work= Tokyohive|publisher= 6Theory Media}}</ref> The group's 35th single, \"[[Mae shika Mukanee]]\", was released on February 26 and sold 970,413 copies on its first day.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.kingrecords.co.jp/cs/t/t4356|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140201201116/http://www.kingrecords.co.jp/cs/t/t4356/|script-title=ja:AKB48 35th\u30b7\u30f3\u30b0\u30eb \u8a73\u7d30\u6c7a\u5b9a\u306e\u304a\u77e5\u3089\u305b|archivedate=February 1, 2014|accessdate=November 5, 2015|publisher=King Records|language=Japanese}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.tokyohive.com/article/2014/01/akb48-reveals-the-details-on-their-35th-single|title= AKB48 reveals the details on their 35th single|date= January 24, 2014|accessdate= January 27, 2014|work= Tokyohive|publisher= 6Theory Media}}</ref>\n\nAKB48 announced plans for a fifth team, Team 8, with one member from each of Japan's 47 prefectures.<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.tokyohive.com/article/2014/01/akb48-announces-the-creation-of-team-8-with-a-new-concept|title= AKB48 announces the creation of 'Team 8' with a new concept|date= January 23, 2014|accessdate= January 27, 2014|work= Tokyohive|publisher= 6Theory Media}} references Oricon {{cite web | url =http://www.oricon.co.jp/news/video/2033276/full/ | title =\u3010\u52d5\u753b\u3011AKB\u300c\u4f1a\u3044\u306b\u884c\u304f\u300d\u65b0\u30c1\u30fc\u30e08\u7d50\u6210 3\u6708\u767a\u8db3\u30018\u6708\u5287\u5834\u30c7\u30d3\u30e5\u30fc\u3078 |trans-title=Launching March 8, a \"go to see\" AKB48 new team, to August theater debut | language = Japanese | date =January 23, 2014 | work = Oricon }}</ref> On February 24, during the group's Grand Reformation Festival event at [[Zepp]] DiverCity Tokyo, the group announced a team reorganization. This included a captain and co-captain of each team, promotion of AKB48 trainees to regular membership (with assignment to the four teams) and the transfer of members between AKB48 and its sister groups.<ref name=\"akb48grandreformation\">{{cite web|url=http://www.akb48.co.jp/page/daisokaku/list.php?after=1&group=akb48|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140227172449/http://www.akb48.co.jp/page/daisokaku/list.php?after=1&group=akb48|script-title=ja:AKB48\u516c\u5f0f\u30b5\u30a4\u30c8\uff5cAKB48\u30b0\u30eb\u30fc\u30d7\u5927\u7d44\u95a3\u796d\u308a|trans-title=AKB48 Official Site \u2013 AKB48 Group Grand Reformation Festival Results|archivedate=February 27, 2014|accessdate=November 5, 2015|publisher=AKB48 Official Website|language=Japanese}}</ref> On April 3 AKB48 introduced its 47-member Team 8<ref name=\"japanized_world-201401\">{{cite web|url=http://japanizedworld.com/2014/01/new-team-for-the-akb48/|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140422233129/http://japanizedworld.com/2014/01/new-team-for-the-akb48/|title=New Team for the AKB48|archivedate=April 22, 2014 |accessdate=November 5, 2015|publisher=Japanized World|language=Japanese}}</ref> as \"the idols who come to you\".<ref name=\"japanized_world-201401\"/><ref group=\"note\">The debut of Team 8 was the first time the group has featured an idol from the [[Ishikawa Prefecture|Ishikawa]], [[Tottori Prefecture|Tottori]], [[Toyama Prefecture|Toyama]], [[Tokushima Prefecture|Tokushima]], [[Yamagata Prefecture|Yamagata]], [[Okayama]], [[K\u014dchi Prefecture|K\u014dchi]], and [[Okinawa Prefecture|Okinawa]] prefectures.</ref> Akimoto announced auditions for an Otona adult member over 30 years old, to participate in events and be the centerpiece of a Glico Papico commercial. On April 16, AKB48 announced the Otona member: Mariko Tsukamoto, a 37-year-old housewife and mother of two.<ref name=\"oricon3\">{{cite web|url=http://www.oricon.co.jp/news/2036509/full/ |title=\"\u5927\u4ebaAKB\"\u585a\u672c\u3055\u3093\u3001\u611b\u79f0\u306f\u300c\u307e\u308a\u308a\u300d \u3071\u308b\u308b\u304c\u547d\u540d (\uff21\uff2b\uff22\uff14\uff18) \u30cb\u30e5\u30fc\u30b9-ORICON STYLE |publisher=Oricon.co.jp |date=April 17, 2014 |accessdate=April 21, 2014}}</ref>\n\nOn May 21 the group released its 36th single, \"[[Labrador Retriever (song)|Labrador Retriever]]\", which sold over 1,462,000 copies on its first day.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://woman.infoseek.co.jp/news/entertainment/oricon_2037662|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140527084137/http://woman.infoseek.co.jp/news/entertainment/oricon_2037662/|script-title=ja:\u3010\u30aa\u30ea\u30b3\u30f3\u3011AKB\u65b0\u66f2\u304c\u521d\u65e5\u58f2\u4e0a\u6b74\u4ee3\u6700\u9ad8146.2\u4e07\u679a \u521d\u65e5\u30df\u30ea\u30aa\u30f3\u306f7\u4f5c\u76ee \u2013 \u82b8\u80fd \u2013 \u6700\u65b0\u30cb\u30e5\u30fc\u30b9\u4e00\u89a7 \u2013 \u697d\u5929WOMAN|archivedate=May 27, 2014|accessdate=November 5, 2015|publisher=Woman.infoseek.co.jp|language=Japanese}}</ref>\n\nOn June 7, AKB48 and its related groups announced the results of the annual election to determine the lineup for its 37th single. The winner was Mayu Watanabe with 159,854 votes, and Rino Sashihara was runner-up with 141,954 votes. The top eighty candidates were ranked in five groups of sixteen.<ref name=\"election2014\">{{cite web|url=http://www.akb48.co.jp/sousenkyo/37thsingle/result.php |title=\u300cAKB48 37th\u30b7\u30f3\u30b0\u30eb \u9078\u629c\u7dcf\u9078\u6319\u300d\u958b\u7968\u7d50\u679c\u306f\u3053\u3061\u3089 |trans-title=\"AKB48 37th single selection general election\" vote counting result is here | work = AKB48 Official Website | language = Japanese |accessdate=June 9, 2014}}</ref>\n\nIn August, AKB48 announced the Baito AKB project, which allows girls to join AKB48 part-time using the job search site Baitoru.<ref name=\"japantoday 20140812\">{{cite web|url=http://www.japantoday.com/category/entertainment/view/akb48-recruiting-part-timers-for-y1000-per-hour|title=AKB48 recruiting part-timers for Y1,000 per hour | work = [[Japan Today]] | date=August 12, 2014 }}</ref> 13,246 girls applied for Baito AKB, and after several screening rounds, 53 girls were selected to sign a five-month contract with a possible three-month extension in February.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://nihongogo.com/2014/10/53-girls-recruited-through-akb48s-baito-akb-part-time-job-campaign/|author=Jeffrey T. | date=October 3, 2014 | title=53 Girls Recruited Through AKB48\u2032s \"Baito AKB\" Part Time Job Campaign|work=Nihongogo.com}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://natalie.mu/music/news/126784|title=\u300c\u30d0\u30a4\u30c8AKB\u300d53\u540d\u304c\u5408\u683c\u5185\u5b9a\u3001\u65b0CM\u51fa\u6f14\u3082|author=Natasha, Inc.|work=natalie.mu|language=Japanese}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tokyohive.com/article/2014/09/53-girls-recruited-for-baito-akb-to-appear-in-cm|title=53 girls recruited for 'Baito AKB' + to appear in CM|work=Tokyohive | publisher=6Theory Media}}</ref> After the end of the project, 11 of the former Baito AKB members entered the yearly Draft Kaigi event aiming to become full members,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.oricon.co.jp/news/2049284/full/|title=AKB\u30c9\u30e9\u30d5\u30c8\u5019\u88dc\u751f49\u4eba\u6c7a\u5b9a \u6771\u4eac\u5973\u5b50\u6d41\u30fb\u5c71\u908a\u306e\u59b9\u3001\u30d0\u30a4\u30c8AKB11\u4eba\u3082 }}</ref> while others expressed their desire to take part in the auditions for the newly planned [[NGT48]] group.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.oricon.co.jp/news/2049326/full/|title=\u30d0\u30a4\u30c8AKB\u6700\u521d\u3067\u6700\u5f8c\u306e\u5287\u5834\u516c\u6f14! \u30c9\u30e9\u30d5\u30c8\u6311\u6226\u3001\u30b9\u30bf\u30c3\u30d5\u8ee2\u5411\u3068\u9078\u3076\u9053\u306f\u69d8\u3005 }}</ref>\n\nOn December 8, long-time member and general manager [[Minami Takahashi]] announced she will leave the group in December 2015 for the group's tenth anniversary.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.japantoday.com/category/entertainment/view/minami-takahashi-to-graduate-from-akb48-in-dec-2015|title=Minami Takahashi to graduate from AKB48 in Dec 2015 | work=[[Japan Today]] | date=December 10, 2015 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sbs.com.au/popasia/blog/2014/12/09/what-it-be-general-manager-akb48-takahashi-minami-explains-her-graduation-speech|title=What is it like to be the general manager of AKB48? Takahashi Minami explains in her graduation speech|work=SBS PopAsia | date=December 9, 2014 | author=SBS PopAsia HQ }}</ref> She recommended that Team K captain [[Yui Yokoyama]] be her successor.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nikkansports.com/entertainment/akb48/news/f-et-tp0-20141208-1406562.html |title=\u300c\u30d0\u30c8\u30f3\u3064\u306a\u3052\u305f\u3044\u300d\u305f\u304b\u307f\u306a\u5352\u696d\u5ba3\u8a00\u5168\u6587 |publisher=nikkansports.com |date=December 8, 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sponichi.co.jp/entertainment/news/2014/12/08/kiji/K20141208009426690.html |title=\u305f\u304b\u307f\u306a\"\u672c\u5f53\u306b\"\uff21\uff2b\uff22\u5352\u696d\u767a\u8868\u3001\u5f8c\u4efb\u7dcf\u76e3\u7763\u306b\u6a2a\u5c71\u7531\u4f9d\u6307\u540d |publisher=sponichi.co.jp |date=December 8, 2014}}</ref>\n\nThe group ranked second overall in Oricon's Artist Total Sales Revenue for the 2014 year, with [[Japanese yen|\u00a5]]13.075 billion.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.oricon.co.jp/special/47530/6/|script-title=ja:2014\u5e74 \u5e74\u9593\u97f3\u697d\uff06\u6620\u50cf\u30e9\u30f3\u30ad\u30f3\u30b0\u767a\u8868 6\u30da\u30fc\u30b8\u76ee|work=Oricon Style | date = December 20, 2014 | accessdate=February 4, 2015 | language=Japanese |trans-title=2014 annual music & video rankings announced sixth page | layurl=http://www.tokyohive.com/article/2014/12/2014-oricon-yearly-artist-total-sales-ranking-top5- | laysource=Tokyohive }}</ref>\n\n====Assault at handshake event====\n{{main|2014 AKB48 handsaw assault}}\nAt a May 25, 2014 handshake event at the Iwate Industry Culture and Convention Center in [[Takizawa, Iwate]], group members [[Rina Kawaei]], [[Anna Iriyama]] and a staff member were attacked by a 24-year-old man with a handsaw. The suspect was arrested for [[attempted murder]],<ref group=\"note\">\nThe assailant was revealed to be an unemployed man who had no previous interest or fan connection to AKB48. He was frustrated that such idols were well-paid. In December 2014, he pleaded guilty to charges of bodily injury and infringement of weapon regulations.\n* {{cite news\n |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140526233612/http://www3.nhk.or.jp/news/html/20140527/t10014748481000.html\n |script-title=ja:\u300c\uff21\uff2b\uff22\u306b\u7279\u5225\u306a\u601d\u3044\u5165\u308c\u306a\u3044\u300d\u3068\u4f9b\u8ff0\n |language=Japanese\n |archivedate=May 26, 2014\n |url-status = dead\n |date=May 26, 2014\n |work=NHK\n |url=http://www3.nhk.or.jp/news/html/20140527/t10014748481000.html\n |df=mdy\n}}\n* {{cite news\n |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140525154928/http://mainichi.jp/select/news/20140526k0000m040112000c.html\n |script-title=ja:\uff21\uff2b\uff22\u8972\u6483:\u5bb9\u7591\u8005\u306e\u6bcd\u300c\u5927\u5909\u306a\u3053\u3068\u3092\u3057\u305f\u300d\u3000\u643a\u5e2f\u901a\u3058\u305a\n |language=Japanese\n |archivedate=May 25, 2014\n |url-status = dead\n |date=May 26, 2015\n |work=Manichi\n |url=http://mainichi.jp/select/news/20140526k0000m040112000c.html\n |df=mdy\n}}\n* {{cite news\n |url=http://www.japantimes.co.jp/news/2014/11/05/national/crime-legal/man-who-attacked-akb-members-with-saw-pleads-guilty/\n |title=Man who attacked AKB48 members with saw pleads guilty\n |date=November 5, 2014\n |work=[[The Japan Times]]\n}}</ref> and the three were treated at a hospital for fractures and cuts.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nikkansports.com/entertainment/akb48/news/f-et-tp0-20140525-1306834.html |title=\u5ddd\u6804\u3001\u5165\u5c71\u8972\u308f\u308c\u305f\uff01\uff21\uff2b\uff22\u63e1\u624b\u4f1a\u306b\u5203\u7269\u7537 |publisher=nikkansports.com |date=May 24, 2014 |accessdate=May 24, 2014}}<br>{{cite web|url=http://www.asahi.com/and_w/interest/entertainment/CORI2037815.html|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140525233405/http://www.asahi.com/and_w/interest/entertainment/CORI2037815.html|script-title=ja:AKB\u63e1\u624b\u4f1a\u4e3b\u50ac\u306e\u30ad\u30f3\u30b0\u30ec\u30b3\u30fc\u30c9\u300c\u5351\u52a3\u306a\u72af\u4eba\u306e\u884c\u70ba\u306b\u6012\u308a\u300d\u3000100\u4eba\u306e\u8b66\u5099\u4f53\u5236\u3082\u8aac\u660e|archivedate=May 25, 2014|accessdate=November 5, 2015|publisher=Asahi Simbum|language=Japanese}}<br>{{cite web|url=http://www.japantoday.com/category/crime/view/akb48-singer-2-staff-members-slashed-at-handshake-event-in-iwate |archive-url=https://archive.today/20140525204048/http://www.japantoday.com/category/crime/view/akb48-singer-2-staff-members-slashed-at-handshake-event-in-iwate |url-status = dead|archive-date=May 25, 2014 |title=Two AKB48 singers, 1 staff member attacked at handshake event in Iwate |publisher=Japan Today |date=May 24, 2014 |accessdate=May 24, 2014 }}<br>{{cite news|agency  = AFP | location = Tokyo | url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2014/may/26/japanese-girl-band-members-attacked-saw-fan-event |title=Japanese girl band AKB48 attacked with a saw at fan event |work=The Guardian |date=May 25, 2014 |accessdate=May 25, 2014}}<br>{{cite news|url=http://www.thejakartaglobe.com/features/slasher-attacks-japan-pop-girl-group-akb48-fan-event |title=Slasher Attacks Japan Pop Girl Group AKB48 at Fan Event |agency = Reuters | publisher=Jakarta Globe |date=May 26, 2014| accessdate=May 26, 2014}}<br>{{cite news|url=http://rt.com/news/161420-japan-akb48-attack-saw/|title=Japanese horror Two pop idols attacked by saw-wielding man|work=[[Russia Today|RT News]]|date=2014-05-25}}<br>{{cite news|url=http://www.japantimes.co.jp/news/2014/05/25/national/crime-legal/akb48-dancers-attacked-saw-wielding-man/|title=AKB48 members attacked by saw-wielding man |newspaper=[[The Japan Times]] |date=2014-05-25}}<br>{{cite news |url= http://mdpr.jp/news/detail/1367044 |title=AKB48\u5165\u5c71\u674f\u5948\u304c\u8972\u308f\u308c\u8ca0\u50b7 \u30b0\u30eb\u30fc\u30d7\u968f\u4e00\u306e\u624d\u8272\u517c\u5099\u3001\u30c9\u30e9\u30de\u306b\u6620\u753b\u521d\u4e3b\u6f14\u2026\u3053\u308c\u307e\u3067\u306e\u6d3b\u52d5\u3068\u306f. |publisher= Model Press |date= 2014-05-26 |language= Japanese}}</ref> AKB48 canceled its theater performances through the end of May,<ref name=\"nikkei20140526\">{{cite news|date=May 26, 2014|url=http://www.nikkei.com/article/DGXNASDG26056_W4A520C1CC1000/|title=\u540d\u53e4\u5c4b\u30fb\u5e55\u5f35\u306e\u63e1\u624b\u4f1a\u3092\u5ef6\u671f\u3000AKB48\u5287\u5834\u306f31\u65e5\u307e\u3067\u4f11\u9928|trans-title=Postpone shake-hand events in Nagoya/Makuhari \u2013 AKB48 Theater will be closed until 31st|newspaper=nikkei.com|publisher=Nikkei Inc. | accessdate=May 26, 2014|language=Japanese}}</ref> and handshake and photo-shoot fan events in May and June were postponed.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.kingrecords.co.jp/cs/t/t4997/|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140606232202/http://www.kingrecords.co.jp/cs/t/t4997/|script-title=ja:\uff16\u6708\uff11\uff14\u65e5\uff08\u571f\uff09\u5168\u56fd\u63e1\u624b\u4f1a\u30a4\u30d9\u30f3\u30c8\uff08\u6a2a\u6d5c\u30b9\u30bf\u30b8\u30a2\u30e0\uff09 \uff16\u6708\uff11\uff15\u65e5\uff08\u65e5\uff09\u30fb\uff16\u6708\uff12\uff19\u65e5\uff08\u65e5\uff09\u30d1\u30b7\u30d5\u30a3\u30b3\u6a2a\u6d5c \u5927\u5199\u771f\u4f1a \u958b\u50ac\u5ef6\u671f\u306e\u304a\u8a6b\u3073\u3068\u304a\u77e5\u3089\u305b|archivedate=June 6, 2014 |trans-title=Apology and announcement of postponement of handshake event on Saturday, June 14, and photo shooting events on Sunday at Yokohama Stadium, June 15, and Sunday, June 29 at Pacifico Yokohama|accessdate=November 5, 2015|publisher=KING RECORDS|language=Japanese}}</ref> In response to security concerns,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://abcnews.go.com/Entertainment/wireStory/members-japanese-pop-group-akb48-attacked-23866211 |title=Japan Pop Group AKB48 Cancels Events After Attack |publisher=ABC News |date=May 26, 2014| accessdate=May 26, 2014}}</ref> the [[Manseibashi Police Station]] of the [[Tokyo Metropolitan Police Department]] asked AKS to conduct security checks of audience members at the theater entrance.<ref name=\"nikkei20140526\"/> The man eventually confessed to being jealous of AKB48, screaming \"omae no te ore no te ze\".<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.cnn.com/2015/02/11/world/japan-akb48-attack-sentence/index.html|title=Japanese man sentenced for saw attack on pop stars|author=Junko Ogura and Tim Hume|website=CNN|access-date=2019-01-28}}</ref> Although sister groups SKE48, NMB48 and HKT48 did not suspend their theater performances, they introduced security measures: [[metal detector]]s, not using the theaters' front rows, suspending post-performance \"high-five\" events and increasing the number of security guards.<ref>{{cite news|date=May 27, 2014|url=http://www.sponichi.co.jp/entertainment/news/2014/05/27/kiji/K20140527008243590.html|script-title=ja:\u5404\u5287\u5834\u3067\u91d1\u5c5e\u63a2\u77e5\u6a5f\u3092\u5c0e\u5165\u3001\u5ba2\u5e2d\u306e\u6700\u524d\u5217\u306f\u4f7f\u7528\u7981\u6b62\u306b|trans-title=Metal detectors introduced at each theater, no front-row seats available|newspaper=Sponichi Annex|publisher=SPORTS NIPPON NEWSPAPERS| accessdate=May 27, 2014|language=Japanese}}</ref> On May 30 AKB48 resumed its television appearances,<ref>{{cite news|date=May 30, 2014|url=http://www.nikkansports.com/entertainment/akb48/news/f-et-tp0-20140530-1309680.html|script-title=ja:\u305f\u304b\u307f\u306a\u3001\u3071\u308b\u308b\u3001\uff2d\u30b9\u30c6\u3067\u76ee\u6f64\u307e\u305b\u71b1\u5531|trans-title=Takamina, Paruru, glistening with emotion when they sang at M-Station|newspaper=nikkansports.com|publisher=NIKKAN SPORTS NEWSPAPERS|accessdate=May 31, 2014|language=Japanese}}</ref> and on June 2 the group resumed  theater performances with security measures similar to those of its sister groups.<ref>{{cite news|date=May 31, 2014|url=http://daily.co.jp/newsflash/gossip/2014/05/31/0007009822.shtml|script-title=ja:\uff21\uff2b\uff22\u5287\u5834\uff16\u6708\uff12\u65e5\u304b\u3089\u518d\u958b\u306e\u516c\u5f0f\u767a\u8868|trans-title=Official announcement to reopen AKB48 Theater from June 2|newspaper=Daily Sports Online|publisher=Daily Sports|accessdate=May 31, 2014|language=Japanese}}</ref> Security and bag checks were added at the general-election-results event and Yuko Oshima's graduation concert.<ref name=\"Sanspo20140608\">{{Cite news|date=June 8, 2014|url=http://www.sanspo.com/geino/news/20140608/akb14060805010002-n1.html|script-title=ja:\u5473\u30b9\u30bf\u5927\u96e8\u53b3\u6212...\u624b\u8377\u7269\u691c\u67fb\u54e1106\u4eba\u3001\u91d1\u5c5e\u63a2\u77e5\u6a5f122\u53f0|newspaper=SANSPO.COM|publisher=SANKEI DIGITAL INC.|accessdate=June 8, 2014|language=Japanese}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|date=June 7, 2014|url=http://www.daily.co.jp/newsflash/gossip/2014/06/07/1p_0007030899.shtml|title=AKB\u7dcf\u9078\u6319\u3000\u5927\u96e8...45\u5206\u9045\u308c\u3067\u958b\u6f14|newspaper=DAILY SPORTS ONLINE|publisher=\u30c7\u30a4\u30ea\u30fc\u30b9\u30dd\u30fc\u30c4|accessdate=June 8, 2014}}</ref>\n\n=== 2015: ''Koko ga Rhodes da, Koko de Tobe!'' and ''0 to 1 no Aida'' ===\n<!-- Deleted image removed: [[File:AKB48 Senbatsu 2015.jpg|left|thumb|alt= The AKB48 A-side roster following the 2015 General Election|The AKB48 A-side roster following the 2015 General Election]] -->\nOn January 21, 2015, the group released its sixth studio album, ''[[Koko ga Rhodes da, Koko de Tobe!]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url= http://www.oricon.co.jp/rank/ja/w/2015-02-02/|title=\u9031\u9593\u3000CD\u30a2\u30eb\u30d0\u30e0\u30e9\u30f3\u30ad\u30f3\u30b0 2015\u5e7402\u670802\u65e5\u4ed8|work= Oricon Style|publisher= [[Oricon]]|accessdate= April 19, 2015|language= Japanese}}</ref> On March 4, the group released the single \"[[Green Flash (song)|Green Flash]]\".<ref>{{cite web|script-title=ja:\u3086\u304d\u308a\u3093\u3000\uff13\u6708\u767a\u58f2\u65b0\u66f2\u300c\uff27\uff52\uff45\uff45\uff4e\u3000\uff26\uff4c\uff41\uff53\uff48\u300d\u3067\u521d\u306e\u30bb\u30f3\u30bf\u30fc\u306b|url=http://www.tokyo-sports.co.jp/entame/entertainment/360028/|website=Tokyo Sports|accessdate=January 27, 2015|language=Japanese|date=January 25, 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=AKB48 39th\u30b7\u30f3\u30b0\u30eb\u300cGreen Flash\u300d\u306e\u521d\u65e5\u58f2\u4e0a\u306f860,269\u679a|url=http://akb48-matome.blog.jp/archives/51959820.html|website=AKB48 Matome|accessdate=March 5, 2015|language=Japanese|date=March 4, 2015}}</ref> The group became the first group who sold their 20 consecutive singles in 1 million on the first week. On March 26, member [[Rina Kawaei]] announced her graduation from the group in order to continue her acting career on her own,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sponichi.co.jp/entertainment/news/2015/03/27/kiji/K20150327010059490.html|script-title=ja:\u5ddd\u6804\u674e\u5948\u3000\u7121\u5ff5\u306e\u5352\u696d\u2026\u4eca\u5f8c\u306f\u5973\u512a\u696d\u306b\u5168\u529b\u300c\u5922\u3092\u8ffd\u3044\u304b\u3051\u305f\u3044\u300d|language= Japanese}}</ref> stating that the previous incident and long period of rest brought her to reflect on her future without depending on the group.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nikkansports.com/entertainment/akb48/news/1452681.html|script-title=ja:\u5ddd\u6804\u3001\u5352\u696d\u306f\u300c\u5922\u3092\u53f6\u3048\u305f\u3044\u3068\u601d\u3063\u305f\u304b\u3089\u300d\u300d|language= Japanese}}</ref>\n\nOn May 10, AKB48 was invited to the annual Japan Day festival in New York, their second performance in the city since 2009.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sponichi.co.jp/entertainment/news/2015/05/12/kiji/K20150512010333440.html|script-title=ja:\u3053\u3058\u306f\u308b\u3001\u6b66\u85e4\u5341\u5922\u3089\uff2e\uff39\u306b\uff21\uff2b\uff22\u3001\u30d5\u30a1\u30f35000\u4eba\u96c6\u7d50\u306b\u611f\u52d5|language=Japanese|access-date=2015-05-15|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150514091842/http://www.sponichi.co.jp/entertainment/news/2015/05/12/kiji/K20150512010333440.html|archive-date=2015-05-14|url-status = dead|df=}}</ref> A small away team consisting of members Rina Hirata, Ryoka Oshima, Haruna Kojima, Tomu Mutou, Saho Iwatate and Rina Nozawa performed a total of five songs cheered by a crowd of 5000 attendants.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nikkansports.com/entertainment/akb48/news/1475012.html|script-title=ja:\u3053\u3058\u306f\u308b\u3089\uff2e\uff39\u3067\u300c\u30d8\u30d3\u30ed\u30c6\u300d\u306a\u3069\uff15\u66f2\u62ab\u9732|language= Japanese}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nikkansports.com/entertainment/akb48/news/1475076.html|script-title=ja:\u91cc\u7530\u307e\u3044\u3082\u8208\u596e\u300c\u3059\u3054\u3044\u71b1\u6c17\u300d\uff21\uff2b\uff22\u30fb\uff2e\uff39\u30a4\u30d9\u30f3\u30c8|language= Japanese}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.oricon.co.jp/news/2052689/full/|title=AKB48\u30016\u5e74\u3076\u308aNY\u30e9\u30a4\u30d6\u306b5000\u4eba\u71b1\u72c2 \u91cc\u7530\u307e\u3044\u73fe\u5730\u5831\u544a\u300c\u3082\u306e\u3059\u3054\u3044\u71b1\u6c17\u300d |language= Japanese}}</ref>\n\nOn May 20, the group released the single \"[[Bokutachi wa Tatakawanai]]\".<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.oricon.co.jp/prof/385015/products/1123755/1/|title= \u50d5\u305f\u3061\u306f\u6226\u308f\u306a\u3044(\u521d\u56de\u9650\u5b9a\u76e4/Type A)|accessdate= May 22, 2015|work= Oricon Style|publisher= [[Oricon]]|language= Japanese}}</ref>\n\nJune 6 saw the announcement of the seventh general election results. The event was broadcast live from [[Fukuoka Dome]] on [[Fuji TV]], which reported an average viewer rating of 18.8% with a peak of 23.4%.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://headlines.yahoo.co.jp/hl?a=20150608-00000033-dal-ent|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150612192619/http://headlines.yahoo.co.jp/hl?a=20150608-00000033-dal-ent|script-title=ja:\uff21\uff2b\uff22\u7dcf\u9078\u6319\u3000\u8996\u8074\u7387\uff11\uff18\u30fb\uff18\uff05\u2026\u904e\u53bb\uff12\u4f4d\u3000\u77ac\u9593\u6700\u9ad8\u306f\u6307\u539f\u30b3\u30fc\u30eb\u3067\uff12\uff13\u30fb\uff14\uff05|archivedate=June 12, 2015|accessdate=November 5, 2015|publisher=Yahoo Japan Corporation|language=Japanese}}</ref> A record 3.2 million votes were cast,<ref name=\"The Japan Times\">{{cite web|url=http://www.japantimes.co.jp/culture/2015/06/08/music/rino-sashihara-crowned-amid-tears-jeers-akb-election/#.VYrQRWA2U0s|title=Rino Sashihara crowned amid tears and jeers at AKB election|author=|date=|work=The Japan Times|accessdate=June 24, 2015}}</ref> with [[Rino Sashihara]] winning the poll for the second time with a record 194,049 votes.<ref>{{cite web|title=\u300cAKB48 41st\u30b7\u30f3\u30b0\u30eb \u9078\u629c\u7dcf\u9078\u6319\u300d\u958b\u7968\u7d50\u679c|url=http://ameblo.jp/akihabara48/entry-12035852788.html|website=AKB48 official blog|publisher=AKB48|accessdate=June 11, 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://sousenkyo.akb48.co.jp/result.php|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150626124741/http://sousenkyo.akb48.co.jp/result.php|script-title=ja:AKB48 10th anniversary year 41st\u30b7\u30f3\u30b0\u30eb \u9078\u629c\u7dcf\u9078\u6319|archivedate=June 26, 2015|accessdate=November 5, 2015|publisher=AKB48|language=Japanese}}</ref>\n\nOn August 26, the group released the single \"[[Halloween Night (song)|Halloween Night]]\".\n\nOn October 25, 2015, during the handshake and autograph event at Pacific Yokohama had announced the details of AKB48's [[Kuchibiru ni Be My Baby|42nd Single]] and Request Hour 2016. The 42nd single was released on December 9, 2015. [[Minami Takahashi]] was the Center in what will be her final appearance on an AKB48 single.<ref>{{cite web|title=Announcement of Minami Takahashi to be Center on her final AKB48 single|url=http://tokyogirlsupdate.com/akb48-42nd-single-details-20151063808.html|website=Tokyo Girls Update|accessdate=October 27, 2015}}</ref>\n\nOn  November 18, the group released its 7th album, ''[[0 to 1 no Aida]]''. This album marks the 10th anniversary of Japanese group, founded in 2005.\n\nThe group's 42nd single \"[[Kuchibiru ni Be My Baby]]\" sold 813,044 copies on its first day of release. This brought their combined single sales to over 36,158,000 single albums sold, making them the artist with the highest number of single album sales in Japan, surpassing rock group [[B'z]].<ref>{{cite news|title=AKB48 overtakes iconic rock group to become Japan's No.1|url=http://www.sbs.com.au/popasia/blog/2015/12/10/akb48-overtakes-iconic-rock-group-become-japans-no1|accessdate=December 11, 2015|publisher=SBS PopAsia HQ|date=December 10, 2015}}</ref>\n\n=== 2016\u20132017: ''Thumbnail'' ===\nOn January 24, 2016, during the final day of the Request Hour 2016 at Tokyo Dome City, AKB48 performed their 43rd single \"[[Kimi wa Melody]]\" which released on March 9, 2016.<ref>{{cite news|title=AKB48's 43rd Single \"Kimi wa Melody\" revealed on the final day of Request Hour 2016!|url=http://tokyogirlsupdate.com/sakura-akb48-43rd-kimi-wa-melody-20160176740.html|accessdate=January 11, 2016|publisher=Tokyo Girls Update|date=January 25, 2016}}</ref> Kimi Wa Melody is the second single to bring back graduates [[Atsuko Maeda]], [[Yuko Oshima]], [[Mariko Shinoda]] and [[Tomomi Itano]] being featured on the main track. The single was  centred by [[Sakura Miyawaki]] being her first time to have a solo centre on an AKB48 track.\n\nIn February 2016, a Taiwanese girl [[Ma Chia-ling|Chia-ling Ma]] was added to the group as \"Taiwan Kenkyusei\". This is the first foreign member in the group.<ref>{{cite news|title=\u3010\uff21\uff2b\uff22\u7d05\u767d\u3011\u53f0\u6e7e\u30aa\u30fc\u30c7\u30a3\u30b7\u30e7\u30f3\u5408\u683c\u306e\u99ac\u5609\u4f36\u300c\u30d8\u30d3\u30ed\u30c6\u300d\uff11\u4eba\u3067\u71b1\u5531|url=http://www.tokyo-sports.co.jp/entame/entertainment/483888/|accessdate=April 2, 2016|publisher=tokyo-sports}}</ref>\n\nOn June 1, 2016, the group released the 44th single \"[[Tsubasa wa Iranai]]\", the single included ballots for the group's General Election for that year. Results of the election were announced on June 18 at the [[Niigata Prefectural Baseball Stadium|Hard Off Eco Stadium]] in Niigata on BS Sky TV Premium and [[Fuji Television|Fuji TV]], where Rino Sashihara placed first with 243,011 votes.{{citation needed|date=February 2017}}  On August 31, the group released the 45th single \"[[LOVE TRIP / Shiawase wo Wakenasai]]\".\n\nOn October 3, [[Haruka Shimazaki]] announced her graduation from AKB48 during a new TV commercial presentation of ''Baitoru''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sponichi.co.jp/entertainment/news/2016/10/03/kiji/K20161003013469290.html|script-title=ja:\u5cf6\u5d0e\u9065\u9999 AKB48\u5e74\u5185\u5352\u696d\u3092\u767a\u8868 \u8ff7\u3063\u305f\u672b\u306e\u6c7a\u65ad \u5973\u512a\u696d\u306b\u524d\u5411\u304d|date=October 3, 2016|accessdate=October 8, 2016|publisher=Sports Nippon Newspapers|language=Japanese}}</ref> On November 16, the group released the 46th single \"[[High Tension (song)|High Tension]]\".\n\nOn December 12, [[Mayu Watanabe]], Rina Izuta and Saya Kawamoto announced a new subsidiary to the AKB48 group known as 'AKB48 China' during a Shanghai press conference and fan meet.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://m.weibo.cn/u/3926472191|title=\u5fae\u535a|website=m.weibo.cn|access-date=December 21, 2016}}</ref> Unlike the established Shanghai sister group [[SNH48]], AKB48 China will act as bridge between Japan and China, bringing Japanese members to the upcoming AKB48 China Theatre. Upcoming promotions include a television drama being filmed and a new online game.{{citation needed|date=February 2017}}\n\nOn January 25, 2017, the group released the eighth studio album ''[[Thumbnail (album)|Thumbnail]]''.<ref>{{cite web |url= http://aramajapan.com/news/rino-sashihara-and-morning-musume-collab-on-akb48s-8th-album/68569/|title= Rino Sashihara and Morning Musume Collab on AKB48\u2019s 8th Album|accessdate= December 26, 2016|work= Arama! Japan }}</ref> On March 15, the group released their 47th single \"[[Shoot Sign]]\", and [[Haruna Kojima]] announced she would be graduating.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tokyohive.com/article/2016/06/kojima-haruna-announces-graduation-from-akb48- |title=Kojima Haruna announces graduation from AKB48 |publisher=tokyohive.com |date=2016-06-20 |accessdate=2019-02-18}}</ref> On May 31, the group released their 48th single ''[[Negaigoto no Mochigusare]]'', which contained ballots for the general election. [[Rino Sashihara]] won the poll for the third consecutive year, this time with 246,376 votes,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/interest/2017-06-21/marriage-graduation-announcements-overshadow-idol-rino-sashihara-3rd-akb48-election-win/.117695|title=Marriage, Graduation Announcements Overshadow Idol Rino Sashihara's 3rd AKB48 Election Win|publisher=}}</ref> and served as the center performer for their 49th single \"[[Sukinanda|#sukinanda]]\", released on August 30. On November 22, their 40th single \"[[11gatsu no Anklet]]\" was released. At the December 2017 team shuffle event, it was announced that the Team 8 members are to hold concurrent positions ({{nihongo3||\u517c\u4efb|kennin}}) with one of the other AKB48 Teams A, K, B, and 4.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://odonsalvatore.blogspot.com/2017/12/details-on-akb48-shuffle-team-members.html|title=Details on AKB48 Shuffle Team Members in late 2017|author=|date=|website=odonsalvatore.blogspot.com|accessdate=July 25, 2018}}</ref> Mayu Watanabe graduated from the group at the end of the year.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.oricon.co.jp/news/2103464/full/|title=\u3010\u7d05\u767d\u3011AKB48\u307e\u3086\u3086\u304c\u6709\u7d42\u306e\u7f8e \u8996\u8074\u8005\u4eba\u6c171\u4f4d\u306f\u300c11\u6708\u306e\u30a2\u30f3\u30af\u30ec\u30c3\u30c8\u300d|language=Japanese|date=31 December 2017|work=[[Oricon|Oricon News]]|publisher=Oircon ME|accessdate=11 April 2018}}</ref>\n\n=== 2018\u2013present: ''Bokutachi wa, Ano Hi no Yoake o Shitteiru'' ===\nIn June, 39 members of AKB48 and their sister groups participated in the South Korean television competition ''[[Produce 48]]'', from which a [[Iz One|IZ*ONE]] was formed. [[Miyawaki Sakura]], [[Yabuki Nako]], [[Hitomi Honda]] finished high enough to earn a spot in the group.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://entertain.naver.com/read?oid=241&aid=0002774723|script-title=ko:[\ub2e8\ub3c5] \u97d3\u65e5\ub370\ubdd4 '\ud504\ub85c\ub4c0\uc2a448' \uac78\uadf8\ub8f9, 2\ub144 6\uac1c\uc6d4 \uacc4\uc57d \ud655\uc815|access-date=2018-04-12|language=ko}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.xportsnews.com/jenter/?ac=article_view&entry_id=919012|title=[\uacf5\uc2dd\uc785\uc7a5] \"'\ud504\ub4c0'\u00b7'AKB48' \uceec\ub798\ubc84\"\u2026'\ud504\ub85c\ub4c0\uc2a448' \ub0b4\ub144 \ubc29\uc1a1 \ud655\uc815|work=X Sports News|date=November 29, 2017|access-date=July 22, 2018|language=ko}}</ref>  For the first time, [[Jurina Matsui]] topped the 10th installment of the AKB48 general elections with 194,453 votes.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.sbs.com.au/popasia/blog/2018/06/18/jurina-matsui-triumphs-2018-akb48-general-election |title=Jurina Matsui triumphs in the 2018 AKB48 General Election &#124; SBS PopAsia |publisher=Sbs.com.au |date=2018-06-18 |accessdate=2019-02-18}}</ref> In July, the RIAJ certified \"Teacher Teacher\" as a triple million, making the group the first girl group to achieve it.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.riaj.or.jp/f/data/cert/gd.html|title=\u4e00\u822c\u793e\u56e3\u6cd5\u4eba \u65e5\u672c\u30ec\u30b3\u30fc\u30c9\u5354\u4f1a|website=www.riaj.or.jp|access-date=2018-07-31}}</ref> Shortly after Produce 48, [[Stone Music Entertainment]] and [[Genie Music]] signed a deal with King Records and AKS and became the official digital distributors of AKB singles in South Korea.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.melon.com/album/detail.htm?albumId=10211449|title=\u30bb\u30f3\u30c1\u30e1\u30f3\u30bf\u30eb\u30c8\u30ec\u30a4\u30f3  (Type B)|website=www.melon.com|language=ko|access-date=2018-11-02}}</ref> On March 13, 2019, the group's 55th single \"[[Jiwaru Days]]\" was released, with Rino Sashihara serving as the center performer in her last single with AKB48. The single's third song arose from a collaboration between AKB48, [[Nogizaka46]] and [[Iz One|IZ*ONE]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://akb.kingrecords.co.jp/cd/akb48_55th_1.html|title=AKB48 55th\u30b7\u30f3\u30b0\u30eb\u53ce\u9332\u5185\u5bb9\u4e00\u90e8\u6c7a\u5b9a\u306e\u304a\u77e5\u3089\u305b {{!}} AKB48 KING RECORDS official website|website=akb.kingrecords.co.jp|language=ja|access-date=2019-02-04}}{{Dead link|date=September 2019 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> On September 18, 2019, the group released the 56th single \"[[Sustainable (song)|Sustainable]]\", their first release of the [[Reiwa period]] and first in six months. On October 19, 2019, AKB48 held a concert in [[Taipei Arena]] with [[AKB48 Team TP]].<ref>{{cite web |title=AKB48 in Taipei 2019 \u301c Are You Ready For It? |url=https://www.eventernote.com/events/215079}}</ref>\n\nFollowing the [[Assault of Maho Yamaguchi|assault on NGT48 member Maho Yamaguchi]], the management of AKB48 faced severe public criticism. The year 2019 marked some major changes for the group, as [[AKBingo]] and [[AKB48 Show!]], two long running nationally broadcast variety shows featuring the group, were eventually cancelled.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://mdpr.jp/news/detail/1862196|title=AKB48\u51a0\u756a\u7d44\u300cAKBINGO\uff01\u300d\u7d42\u4e86\u3078\u300011\u5e74\u534a\u306e\u6b74\u53f2\u306b\u5e55|website=www.mdpr.jp|language=ja|access-date=2020-01-30}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nhk.or.jp/akb48show-blog/100/314789.html|title=\u756a\u7d44\u3092\u5fdc\u63f4\u3057\u3066\u304f\u3060\u3055\u3063\u305f\u7686\u3055\u3093\u3078|website=www.nhk.or.jp|language=ja|access-date=2020-01-30}}</ref> The Akihabara-based AKB48 Cafe and Shop was closed after eight years of operation.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2019-11-19/akb48-cafe-and-shop-in-akihabara-closes-after-8-years/.153441|title=AKB48 Cafe & Shop in Akihabara Closes After 8 Years|website=www.animenewsnetwork.com|language=en|access-date=2020-01-30}}</ref> In 2019, three regular annual events were discontinued, including the general election,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nikkansports.com/entertainment/akb48/news/201903130001064.html|title=\uff21\uff2b\uff22\u7dcf\u9078\u6319\u306e\u958b\u50ac\u898b\u9001\u308a\u767a\u8868\u300009\u5e74\u958b\u59cb\u4ee5\u964d\u3067\u521d|website=www.nikkansports.com|language=ja|access-date=2020-01-30}}</ref> and for the first time in the group's history, only two singles were released in a year. 2020 began with the announcement of plans to significantly change AKB48 management structures, with individual companies independently running each of the Japanese groups.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.allkpop.com/article/2020/01/akb48s-japanese-company-announces-division-of-management-in-preparation-for-izones-return-to-promotions|title=AKB48's Japanese company announces division of management in preparation for IZ*ONE's return to promotions|website=www.allkpop.com|language=en|access-date=2020-01-30}}</ref> On March 18, 2020, the group released the 57th single \"[[Shitsuren, Arigat\u014d]]\".\n\n== Musical style ==\nMonica Hesse of ''[[The Washington Post]]'' described the group's style: \"It is as if [[Miley Cyrus]], [[Taylor Swift]] and the entire cast of [[The Twilight Saga (film series)|''Twilight'']] were placed into a saucepan and simmered on a low boil until nothing remained but the sweet, cloying essence of fame, and if that fame were then poured into pleated tartan skirts and given pigtails.\"<ref name=\"washingtonpost20120327\"/> Andrew Joyce and Kenneth Maxwell of ''[[The Wall Street Journal]]'' described the music as \"sugar-sweet pop tunes and sometimes-suggestive lyrics\". During AKB48 performances, \"members perform a revue of simply choreographed routines in front of a roughly 95-percent-male audience. The music is typical Japanese pop: fast-paced numbers with high-pitched, singalong choruses.\"<ref name=\"wsj20111228\">{{cite news|last=Joyce |first=Andrew |url=https://www.wsj.com/articles/SB10001424052970203733304577101733547361496 |title=Japan Goes Gaga Over AKB48, a 92-Member Girl Group - WSJ.com |publisher=Online.wsj.com |date=December 28, 2011 |accessdate=April 25, 2013}}</ref>\n\n== Promotion and media ==\nAKB48 and its sister groups boost their record sales by a variety of marketing strategies. The main track for each single is recorded by a team of {{Nihongo|\"All Stars\"|\u9078\u629c|senbatsu|selection}} consisting of popular members from AKB48's teams and sister groups, with one of the girls selected as the center performer or Center. This creates a competitive atmosphere between members and fan groups. The singles and albums are released in different editions and types with alternate album-cover pictures, B-side tracks, video DVDs, collectible member pictures, and voting codes for several annual election contests.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://en.rocketnews24.com/2014/12/14/whos-still-buying-physical-media-in-japan-top-20-singles-lists-for-the-year-reveal-the-answer |title=Who\u2019s still buying physical media in Japan? Top 20 singles lists for the year reveal the answer |first=Casey |last=Baseel | publisher=rocketnews24.com |date=December 14, 2014 |accessdate=January 28, 2015}}</ref> Record purchases come with tickets for fan meetings, including so-called handshake events or photo sessions. Customers can choose the members they want to meet in an online pre-order system. All these strategies motivate fans to buy more than one copy of each release.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.sbs.com.au/popasia/blog/2017/10/19/akb48-fan-allegedly-dumps-585-cds-mountain-fukuoka |title=AKB48 fan allegedly dumps 585 CDs on a mountain in Fukuoka  |first=Patrick|last=St. Michael| website=sbs.com |date=October 19, 2017 |accessdate=March 30, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.japantimes.co.jp/culture/2015/12/27/music/future-japanese-music-depend-streaming-services/ |title=Does the future of Japanese music depend on streaming services? |first=Jun|last=Morikawa | website=japantimes.co,jp |date=December 27, 2015 |accessdate=March 30, 2020}}</ref> Alan Swarts of [[MTV Japan]] has noted that collectors purchasing multiple copies of AKB48 CDs have inflated the market, and is one of the reasons Japan's music industry has been booming.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/biz/articles/news/global/1568815/why-japans-music-industry-is-booming-for-now/ |title=Why Japan\u2019s Music Industry Is Booming... For Now |first=Alan |last=Swarts | website=Billboard.com |date=July 23, 2013 |accessdate=May 29, 2014}}</ref>\n\n===Events===\nThe group has publicized special events to choose the promotional and recording lineups for some of its singles.<ref name=\"ap20120612\">{{cite news|title=Japan\u2019s AKB48, a girl pop group whose lineup is chosen by fans, set to go global|url=http://www.nydailynews.com/entertainment/music-arts/japan-akb48-girl-pop-group-lineup-chosen-fans-set-global-article-1.1094083|date=June 12, 2012|agency = Associated Press| publisher=NY Daily News|accessdate=April 7, 2013|location=New York}}</ref> In 2009, the concept of {{nihongo3||\u9078\u629c\u7dcf\u9078\u6319|senbatsu s\u014dsenkyo|\"selection general election\"}} was introduced, which allowed fans to vote their favorite members into the promotional line up for one of their annual singles.<ref name=\"What is AKB48\" /> Ballots are obtained by purchasing the group's latest \"election single\",<ref name=\"japantimes20120531\"/> or, alternatively, through the group's mobile app products and fan club subscriptions.<ref name=\"voting methods 2009\">{{cite web|url=http://ameblo.jp/akihabara48/entry-10260244797.html|title=AKB48 13th\u30b7\u30f3\u30b0\u30eb \u9078\u629c\u7dcf\u9078 |work=AKB48 Official Blog / Ameblo | date=May 13, 2009 }}</ref><ref name=\"japantimes20130701\">{{cite web|url=http://www.japantimes.co.jp/life/2013/07/01/language/voting-for-idols-is-bigger-than-politics/|title=Voting for idols is bigger than politics|work=Japan Times|date=July 1, 2013|first=Minoru|last=Matsutani}}</ref> Top vote getting members are heavily promoted,<ref name=\"japantimes20100824\" /> with the winner getting the centerpiece of the group's live performances of the single.<ref name=\"ap20120612\"/><ref name=\"japantimes20120531\">{{cite web | last1 = St. Michel | first1 = Patrick | last2 = Kikuchi | first2 = Daisuke | url = http://www.japantimes.co.jp/culture/2012/05/31/music/akb48-election-shows-marketing-brilliance/ | title = AKB48 'election' shows marketing brilliance| work = Japan Times| date = May 31, 2012 | page = 17}}</ref> The total pool of votes counted has exceeded three million votes for individual events since 2015.<ref name=\"Oricon_2017_SSK\">{{cite news| url = http://www.oricon.co.jp/news/2092655/full/| title = \u3010\u7b2c9\u56deAKB\u7dcf\u9078\u6319\u3011\u7dcf\u6295\u7968\u6570\u304c\u904e\u53bb\u6700\u591a338\u4e07\u7968\u306b \u30cf\u30d7\u30cb\u30f3\u30b0\u7d9a\u304d\u3082\u8a18\u9332\u66f4\u65b0 | publisher = [[Oricon]]| date = June 17, 2017}}</ref> Fans have reportedly bought hundreds of copies of singles to vote for their favorite members.<ref name=\"wsj20111228\"/><ref name=\"japantimes20120531\" /><ref>{{cite web|last=Beck |first=Julie |url=https://www.theatlantic.com/entertainment/archive/2013/09/lady-gagas-scandalous-attempt-to-rally-fans-j-pop-style/279661/ |title=Lady Gaga's Scandalous Attempt to Rally Fans, J-Pop Style \u2013 Patrick St. Michel |publisher=The Atlantic |date=September 16, 2013 |accessdate=January 14, 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Robertson |first=Adi |url=https://www.theverge.com/2013/2/8/3967268/akb48-minami-minegishi-how-a-j-pop-cult-took-over-japan |title=Dating AKB48: the J-pop cult banned from falling in love |publisher=The Verge |date=February 8, 2013 |accessdate=January 14, 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.businessweek.com/articles/2013-07-03/cds-rule-japans-music-market-thanks-to-girl-groups-and-add-ons |title=CDs Rule Japan's Music Market, Thanks to Girl Groups and Add-Ons |publisher=Businessweek |date=July 3, 2013 |accessdate=January 14, 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://asiancorrespondent.com/83481/akb48-annual-elections-only-a-week-away/ |title=Japan: AKB48 annual elections only a week away |publisher=Asian Correspondent |first=Anna |last=Watanabe|date=May 31, 2012 |accessdate=January 14, 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://kotaku.com/5806153/when-you-have-too-much-money-questionable-judgment-and-like-idols/ |title=When You Have Too Much Money, Questionable Judgment, and Like Idols |publisher=Kotaku.com |date=May 27, 2011 |accessdate=January 14, 2014}}</ref>\n\nAnother selection method, AKB48's rock-paper-scissors tournaments, was introduced in 2010 for the group's 19th single (\"[[Chance no Junban]]\") and has recurred as an annual event.<ref name=\"natalie20101104\">{{cite web| url=http://natalie.mu/music/news/40077 | title=AKB48\u3001\u3058\u3083\u3093\u3051\u3093\u9078\u629c\u30b7\u30f3\u30b0\u30eb\u306f\u300c\u30c1\u30e3\u30f3\u30b9\u306e\u9806\u756a\u300d | work=[[Natalie (website)|Natalie]]| publisher=[[Natasha, Inc.]]| date=November 4, 2010| accessdate=April 21, 2012|language=Japanese}}</ref> Members of AKB48 and its sister groups compete in the [[knockout tournament]] to be part of the recording and promotional lineup for the group's next single,<ref name=\"natalie20110921\">{{cite web| url=http://natalie.mu/music/news/56811 | title=AKB48\u3058\u3083\u3093\u3051\u3093\u9078\u629c\u8a73\u7d30\u30ec\u30dd\u300c\u65b0\u3057\u3044AKB\u306e\u5f62\u898b\u3048\u305f\u300d | work=[[Natalie (website)|Natalie]]| publisher=[[Natasha, Inc.]]| date=September 21, 2011| accessdate=April 21, 2012 |language=Japanese}}</ref> with participants wearing a variety of costumes.<ref name=\"rpsresults2013\"/> Starting with 2014, the tournament does not determine the promotional line up of a single anymore. Instead, the winner would debut as a soloist or, if she was already a soloist, would perform a solo concert.<ref name=\"oricon\">{{cite web| url=http://www.oricon.co.jp/news/2040711/full/ | title=AKB\u3058\u3083\u3093\u3051\u3093\u512a\u52dd\u7279\u5178\u306f\u30bd\u30ed\u30c7\u30d3\u30e5\u30fc | work=[[Oricon]]| publisher=[[Oricon Style]]| date=August 7, 2014| accessdate=September 15, 2012 |language=Japanese}}</ref>\n\nAKB48 has also used the general election scheme to determine set lists for an annual {{nihongo|Request Hour|\u30ea\u30af\u30a8\u30b9\u30c8\u30a2\u30ef\u30fc|rikuesuto aw\u0101}} show.{{citation needed|reason=need source for description of process|date=September 2016}} Other annual events include an AKB48 group only version of [[K\u014dhaku Uta Gassen]]{{citation needed|reason=need source for event establishment|date=September 2016}} and the {{nihongo|AKB group draft meeting|AKB48\u30b0\u30eb\u30fc\u30d7 \u30c9\u30e9\u30d5\u30c8\u4f1a\u8b70|AKB48 gur\u016bpu dorafuto kaigi}}, in which all teams from any of the sister groups chose new members from a pre-selected group of applicants.<ref>{{cite web|url = http://www.akb48.co.jp/akbdraft/|title = AKB48\u516c\u5f0f\u30b5\u30a4\u30c8\uff5cAKB48\u30b0\u30eb\u30fc\u30d7 \u30c9\u30e9\u30d5\u30c8\u4f1a\u8b70|publisher = AKB48|accessdate = January 5, 2016|language = Japanese}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url = http://www.akb48.co.jp/akbdraft_2nd/|title = \u7b2c2\u56deAKB48\u30b0\u30eb\u30fc\u30d7\u30c9\u30e9\u30d5\u30c8\u4f1a\u8b70\u3068\u306f|publisher = AKB48|accessdate = January 5, 2016|language = Japanese}}</ref><br>\n\nIn 2019, the general election, the Janken tournament, and K\u014dhaku Uta Gassen were not held.\n\n===Documentaries===\n\nFour AKB48 documentaries have been released in theaters since 2011. The first, ''Documentary of AKB48 \u2013 To Be Continued'', was released in Japan on January 22, 2011<ref>{{cite web |url= http://eiga.com/movie/55861/|title= DOCUMENTARY of AKB48 to be continued 10\u5e74\u5f8c\u3001\u5c11\u5973\u305f\u3061\u306f\u4eca\u306e\u81ea\u5206\u306b\u4f55\u3092\u601d\u3046\u306e\u3060\u308d\u3046\uff1f|accessdate= January 28, 2014|work= eiga.com|language= Japanese}}</ref> and on DVD in North America on December 1.<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2011-11-14/new-people-entertainment-announces-dvd-release-of-akb48-documentary|title= New People Entertainment Announces DVD Release Of AKB48 Documentary|date= November 14, 2011|accessdate= January 28, 2014|work= [[Anime News Network]]}}</ref> The second, ''Documentary of AKB48: Show Must Go On Sh\u014djo-tachi wa Kizutsuki Nagara, Yume wo Miru'', was released on January 27, 2012<ref name=\"eiga\"/> and earned $3,984,152 at the Japanese box office.<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.boxofficemojo.com/movies/intl/?page=&country=JP&id=_fDOCUMENTARYOFAKB01|title= Documentary of akb48: show must go on|accessdate= August 27, 2014|work= [[Box Office Mojo]]}}</ref> The third, ''Documentary of AKB48: No Flower Without Rain: Sh\u014djo Tachi wa Namida no Ato ni Nani o Miru?'', was released on February 2, 2013<ref>{{cite web |url= http://eiga.com/movie/77715/|title= DOCUMENTARY of AKB48 No flower without rain \u5c11\u5973\u305f\u3061\u306f\u6d99\u306e\u5f8c\u306b\u4f55\u3092\u898b\u308b\uff1f|accessdate= January 28, 2014|work= eiga.com|language= Japanese}}</ref> and earned $2,269,118 at the Japanese box office.<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.boxofficemojo.com/movies/intl/?page=&country=JP&id=_fDOCUMENTARYOFAKB02|title= Documentary of akb48: no flower without rain|accessdate= August 27, 2014|work= [[Box Office Mojo]]}}</ref> The fourth, ''Documentary of AKB48 The Time has come Sh\u014djo-tachi wa, Ima, Sono Senaka ni Nani wo Omou?'', was released on July 4, 2014<ref>{{cite web |url= http://eiga.com/movie/80239/|title= DOCUMENTARY of AKB48 The time has come \u5c11\u5973\u305f\u3061\u306f\u3001\u4eca\u3001\u305d\u306e\u80cc\u4e2d\u306b\u4f55\u3092\u60f3\u3046\uff1f|accessdate= August 26, 2014|work= eiga.com|language= Japanese}}</ref> and (as of July 13, 2014) grossed $984,757 at the Japanese box office.<ref>{{cite web |url= http://boxofficemojo.com/intl/japan/?yr=2014&wk=28&p=.htm|title= Japan Box Office July 12\u201313, 2014|accessdate= August 27, 2014|work= [[Box Office Mojo]]}}</ref> Each film chronicled events and issues encountered by the group during the previous year.<ref name=\"ann20120204\"/> The most recent film was ''Sonzai Suru Riy: Documentary of AKB48'' was released on July 8, 2016.<ref>{{cite web |url= https://eiga.com/movie/81531/|title= \u5b58\u5728\u3059\u308b\u7406\u7531 DOCUMENTARY of AKB48|accessdate= February 13, 2020|work= eiga.com|language= Japanese}}</ref>\n\n===Manga and anime===\nThe manga ''[[AKB49: Ren'ai Kinshi J\u014drei]]'' revolves around AKB48, featuring group members in the story as supporting characters.<ref name=\"cinematoday20100826\">{{cite web|url=http://www.cinematoday.jp/page/N0026476 |title=\u30de\u30f3\u30ac\u300cAKB49\u300d\u306fAKB48\u5927\u5cf6\u512a\u5b50\u3082\u7d0d\u5f97\u306e\u51fa\u6765!?\u300c\u697d\u5c4b\u3067\u306e\u79c1\u306e\u307e\u3093\u307e\u3060((;\u309c\u0414\u309c))\u300d |publisher=Cinema Today |language=Japanese|accessdate=October 23, 2011|date=August 26, 2010}}</ref> The 2012 [[anime]] series ''[[AKB0048]]'' is a science-fiction series based on the group, with production supervised by Yasushi Akimoto.<ref name=\"ann20120420\">{{cite web|url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2012-04-20/akb0048-idol-sci-fi-anime-tv-ad-streamed |title=AKB0048 Idol Sci-Fi Anime's TV Ad Streamed |publisher=Anime News Network |accessdate=May 21, 2012|date=April 20, 2012}}</ref> Nine characters in the anime are voiced by members of AKB48 and its sister groups.<ref name=\"ann20120420\" /> First airing in Japan in the spring of 2012,<ref name=\"ann20120420\" /> a second season was broadcast in 2013.<ref name=ann20121212>{{cite web|title=AKB0048 next stage's 1st Promo Streamed|url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2012-12-12/akb0048-next-stage-1st-promo-streamed|publisher=Anime News Network|accessdate=April 19, 2015|date=December 12, 2012}}</ref>\n\n===Video games===\nThe group has its own [[visual novel]]-[[dating sim]] series. In the first installment, ''AKB1/48: Idol to Koishitara...''  (released December 23, 2010), the player engages in a relationship with one of the members. The second installment, ''AKB1/48: Idol to Guam de Koishitara...'' (released October 10, 2011, with a similar storyline) is set in [[Guam]]. The third installment, ''AKB1/149 Ren'ai S\u014dsenkyo'' (released December 20, 2012), expands the scenarios to AKB48 sister groups SKE48, NMB48 and HKT48. The three games were released for [[PlayStation Portable]], with ''Ren'ai Sousenkyo'' also released for [[PlayStation Vita]] and [[PlayStation 3]].{{citation needed|date=January 2014}} In 2014 [[Namco Bandai]] developed ''Sailor Zombie: AKB48 Arcade Edition'', as a [[tie-in]] for the [http://www.tv-tokyo.co.jp/sailor-zombie/ television drama] going by the same name, in which AKB48 members are also the main cast. In this arcade game, the player must use a light gun to shoot vaccine bullets at zombified AKB48 members. The game includes a [[rhythm game]] in which the zombie idols dance.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.siliconera.com/2014/02/06/akb48-arcade-game-pretty-much-akb48-house-dead/ |title=The AKB48 Arcade Game Is Pretty Much AKB48 House Of The Dead |publisher=Siliconera |date=February 6, 2014 |accessdate=March 31, 2014}}</ref> In April 2014, a rhythm game was released for [[Android (operating system)|Android]] and [[iOS]], in which the players select their favourite line up and may compete in various community events.<ref>{{cite web|url = http://www.siliconera.com/2014/05/07/akb48-finally-gets-official-music-game-well-name-game/|title = AKB48 finally gets an official music game|publisher = Siliconera|date = May 7, 2014|accessdate = January 6, 2015}}</ref> In 2012, ''AKB48+Me'' was published for the [[Nintendo 3DS]], which let the players try to become a member of AKB48.<ref>{{cite web|url = http://www.polygon.com/2012/10/17/3517014/japan-review-check-akb48-borderlands-2-forza-horizon/|title = Japan Review Check: AKB48, Borderlands 2, Forza: Horizon|publisher = Polygon.com|date = October 17, 2012|accessdate = January 6, 2015}}</ref> An ad for ''[[Super Smash Bros. for Nintendo 3DS]]'' also featured [[Mii]]s of the group, specifically showing off member [[Yuki Kashiwagi]] and former members [[Mayu Watanabe]] and [[Minami Takahashi]].<ref>{{cite web|url = https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=J5L6NliO2LQ|title = Super Smash Bros. for 3DS - Japanese Commercial #4! [AKB48 Promotion Video]|publisher = Ndukauba|date = September 7, 2014}}</ref>\n\n===Other media===\n{{see also|AKB48 filmography#TV shows}}\nAKB48's producers have developed several television shows to promote the group. ''[[AKBingo!]]'', ''[[AKB48 Show!]]'', ''AKB to XX'', and ''{{Interlanguage link|Nem\u014dsu TV|ja|AKB48\u30cd\u7533\u30c6\u30ec\u30d3|vertical-align=sup}}'' were variety shows.{{citation needed|date=September 2016}} The ''[[Majisuka Gakuen]]'' series<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/interview/2010-07-08/from-akiba-to-l.a-with-akb48|title=From Akiba to L.A. with AKB48|publisher=|accessdate=March 15, 2017}}</ref> and ''{{Interlanguage link|Sakura Karano Tegami|ja|\u685c\u304b\u3089\u306e\u624b\u7d19 \u301cAKB48 \u305d\u308c\u305e\u308c\u306e\u5352\u696d\u7269\u8a9e\u301c|vertical-align=sup}}'' feature group members in dramatic roles. Outside the self-developed house shows, members of AKB48 have appeared in high-profile programs such as ''[[Mecha-Mecha Iketeru!]]'', ''[[Waratte Iitomo!]]'' or ''[[SMAPxSMAP]]''.{{citation needed|date=September 2016}} Members frequently appear in [[Gravure idol|gravure]] magazines.{{citation needed|date=September 2016}} Since 2016, the streaming platform 'SHOWROOM' collaborates with the AKB48 group and offers a steady supply of rotating group members streaming in private situations.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://campaign.showroom-live.com/akb48_sr/ |title=AKB48 Group x Showroom|publisher=SHOWROOM|accessdate=January 31, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=\nhttps://realsound.jp/2016/10/post-9697.html |title=AKB48\u30b0\u30eb\u30fc\u30d7\u3001SHOWROOM\u306b\u3066\u500b\u4eba\u914d\u4fe1\u30b9\u30bf\u30fc\u30c8\u3000\u30e1\u30f3\u30d0\u30fc\u5404\u81ea\u306e\u597d\u304d\u306a\u30bf\u30a4\u30df\u30f3\u30b0\u3067\u751f\u914d\u4fe1|publisher=realsound|accessdate=January 31, 2020}}</ref>\n\n== Reception ==\nTower Records Japan CEO Ikuo Minewaki described AKB48 as a popular act,<ref name=\"japanrealtime20130624\">{{cite news|url=https://blogs.wsj.com/japanrealtime/2013/06/24/as-cds-spin-on-in-japan-tower-records-rocks-on/|title=As CDs Spin On in Japan, Tower Records Rocks On|publisher=Japan Real Time|date=June 14, 2013|accessdate=July 3, 2013}}</ref> and the group has been characterized as a social phenomenon in Japan.<ref name=\"mantanweb20120506\">{{cite web|url=http://mantan-web.jp/2012/05/06/20120504dog00m200011000c.html|title=\u3082\u3082\u30af\u30ed \uff1a \"\u97f3\u697d\u597d\u304d\"\u306e\u652f\u6301\u3067\u30dd\u30b9\u30c8AKB\u306b\u6025\u6d6e\u4e0a\uff1f\u3000\u7fa4\u96c4\u5272\u62e0\u306e\u30a2\u30a4\u30c9\u30eb\u30b7\u30fc\u30f3|publisher=[[Mainichi Shimbun|Mainichi Shimbun Digital]]|date=May 6, 2012|accessdate=May 18, 2012|language=Japanese}}</ref> In 2012 AKB48 had record sales in Japan of over $226&nbsp;million.<ref name=\"tokyohive201212\">{{cite web|url=http://www.tokyohive.com/article/2012/12/oricon-reveals-artist-total-sales-revenue-ranking-for-2012/|title=Oricon reveals \"Artist Total Sales Revenue\" ranking for 2012|work=Tokyohive|date=December 20, 2012|accessdate=August 5, 2013}} \u2013 references Oricon article</ref> Total sales of over $128&nbsp;million were reported for 2013, and of over $96&nbsp;million in 2015.<ref name=\"tokyohive201312\"/><ref name=\"Oricon2015\">{{cite news|url=http://aramajapan.com/news/music/oricon-unveils-their-yearly-sales-rankings-for-2015/53356//|title=Oricon unveils their Yearly Sales Rankings for 2015|publisher=aramajapan|date=December 21, 2015|accessdate=December 26, 2015}}</ref> According to [[Oricon]], as of January 6, 2012 AKB48 sold a total of 11,787,000 singles, setting a record for \"the most singles sold in Japan by a female group\".<ref name=\"oricon20120106\" /> The group's last 35 singles have topped the weekly [[Oricon Singles Chart]]. In 2010 \"[[Beginner (song)|Beginner]]\" and \"[[Heavy Rotation (song)|Heavy Rotation]]\" placed first and second, respectively, on the list of Japan's bestselling singles of the year;<ref name=\"oriconrankjsy2010\">{{cite web|url=http://www.oricon.co.jp/rank/js/y/|title=\u30b7\u30f3\u30b0\u30eb\u5e74\u9593\u30e9\u30f3\u30ad\u30f3\u30b0-ORICON STYLE \u30e9\u30f3\u30ad\u30f3\u30b0|publisher=Oricon Inc.|accessdate=July 17, 2011|language=Japanese|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110722071123/http://www.oricon.co.jp/rank/js/y/|archivedate=July 22, 2011 |url-status = live}}</ref> From 2010 to 2019, <!-- prior to a retooling of Oricon's counting scheme in 2016 to exclude music cards and bulk CD sales (?) (reference) --> AKB48's singles have occupied at least the top two,<ref name=\"annual_charts\" /> and sometimes the top four or five spots of the Oricon Yearly Singles Chart.<ref name=\"oriconyearly2011\">{{cite web|url=http://www.oricon.co.jp/rank/js/y/2011/|title= \u5e74\u9593\u3000CD\u30b7\u30f3\u30b0\u30eb\u30e9\u30f3\u30ad\u30f3\u30b0 2011\u5e74\u5ea6|publisher=[[Oricon]]|accessdate=February 1, 2017|language=Japanese}}</ref><ref name=\"oriconyearly2012\">{{cite web|url=http://www.oricon.co.jp/rank/js/y/2012/|title= \u5e74\u9593\u3000CD\u30b7\u30f3\u30b0\u30eb\u30e9\u30f3\u30ad\u30f3\u30b0 2012\u5e74\u5ea6|publisher=[[Oricon]]|accessdate=February 1, 2017|language=Japanese}}</ref><ref name=\"oriconyearly2013\">{{cite web|url=http://www.oricon.co.jp/rank/js/y/2013/|title= \u5e74\u9593\u3000CD\u30b7\u30f3\u30b0\u30eb\u30e9\u30f3\u30ad\u30f3\u30b0 2013\u5e74\u5ea6|publisher=[[Oricon]]|accessdate=February 1, 2017|language=Japanese}}</ref><ref name=\"oriconyearly2014\">{{cite web|url=http://www.oricon.co.jp/rank/js/y/2014/|title= \u5e74\u9593\u3000CD\u30b7\u30f3\u30b0\u30eb\u30e9\u30f3\u30ad\u30f3\u30b0 2014\u5e74\u5ea6|publisher=[[Oricon]]|accessdate=February 1, 2017|language=Japanese}}</ref><ref name=\"oriconyearly2015\">{{cite web|url=http://www.oricon.co.jp/rank/js/y/2015/|title= \u5e74\u9593\u3000CD\u30b7\u30f3\u30b0\u30eb\u30e9\u30f3\u30ad\u30f3\u30b0 2015\u5e74\u5ea6|publisher=[[Oricon]]|accessdate=February 1, 2017|language=Japanese}}</ref><ref name=\"oriconyearly2016\">{{cite web|url=http://www.oricon.co.jp/rank/js/y/2016/|title= \u5e74\u9593\u3000CD\u30b7\u30f3\u30b0\u30eb\u30e9\u30f3\u30ad\u30f3\u30b0 2016\u5e74\u5ea6|publisher=[[Oricon]]|accessdate=February 1, 2017|language=Japanese}}</ref> {{As of|2018|6}}, the group has sold over 60&nbsp;million<!--- do not change this figure without updating the sources---> records,<ref name=\"oriconapril2019\" /> including over 6 million albums.<ref name=\"oricon20152411\"/>  AKB48 is the [[List of best-selling music artists in Japan|highest selling musical act in Japan]] in terms of singles sold.<ref name=\"oricon20151209\"/> However, AKB48's 42nd single \"[[Kuchibiru ni Be My Baby]]\" failed to sell more than one million copies in the first week after its release, ending a run of single releases achieving this feat, starting with \"[[Everyday, Katyusha]]\" in 2011.<ref>{{cite web|url = http://www.tnsori.com/20151221-oricon-single-weekly/|title = Oricon weekly (singles)|publisher = The Natsu Style|date = December 15, 2014|accessdate = December 25, 2015}}</ref>\n\nBeside CD sales, AKB48 enjoys commercial success in other areas as well. The group has six singles certificated by [[Recording Industry Association of Japan|RIAJ]] for reaching a million downloads each.<ref>{{cite web |title=\u300c\u604b\u3059\u308b\u30d5\u30a9\u30fc\u30c1\u30e5\u30f3\u30af\u30c3\u30ad\u30fc\u300d\u304c\u3001\u6709\u6599\u97f3\u697d\u914d\u4fe1\u8a8d\u5b9a\u306b\u304a\u3044\u3066\u30df\u30ea\u30aa\u30f3\u306b\u306a\u3063\u305f\u306e\u3067\u3001\u4ed6\u306eAKB48\u66f2\u3092\u542b\u3081\u3066\u8003\u5bdf\u3057\u307e\u3057\u305f |url=http://natuka-shinobu.hatenablog.com/entry/20150421/1429617387}}</ref> According to [[Joysound]], AKB48 has been named the [[karaoke]] artist of the year for four years in a row (2011-2014).<ref>{{cite web |title=2014\u5e74JOYSOUND \u5e74\u9593\u30ab\u30e9\u30aa\u30b1\u30e9\u30f3\u30ad\u30f3\u30b0\u767a\u8868 |url=https://www.joysound.com/web/s/karaoke/contents/annual_ranking/2014}}</ref> In 2011, eight positions of annual top 10 photobook sales were occupied by group members.<ref>{{cite web |title=\u5e74\u9593\u30d2\u30c3\u30c8\u30bf\u30ec\u30f3\u30c8\u672c/\u5199\u771f\u96c6 2011\u5e74(\u5e73\u621023\u5e74) \u30d9\u30b9\u30c810 |url=https://entamedata.web.fc2.com/hobby/hit_book_tare2011.html}}</ref> In 2012, six members topped the individual rankings of advertisement campaigns.<ref>{{cite web |title=\u5e74\u9593CM\u8d77\u7528\u793e\u6570\u3001\u5973\u6027\u4e0a\u4f4d\u306fAKB\u72ec\u5360 |url=https://www.oricon.co.jp/news/2019500/full/}}</ref> AKB48 is also one of the most viewed Japanese artists on Youtube.<ref>{{cite web |title=JPOP NEWS: TOP 10 MOST VIEWED JPOP MUSIC VIDEO |url=https://www.snrcloud.com/jpop-news-top-10-most-viewed-jpop-music-video/#targetText=AKB48%20%E2%80%93%20Koi%20Suru%20Fortune%20Cookie&targetText=It%20involved%203%2C800%20extras.,million%2Dviews%20MVs%20on%20Youtube.}}</ref>\n\nAKB48 holds several [[Guinness World Record]]s, including being recognized on December 1, 2010 as the \"largest pop group\" when it numbered 48 members.<ref name=\"guinnesslargestpopgroup\" /><ref name=\"yeinjee20101115\" /> It set a record for \"most number of same-product television endorsements within 24 hours\" on February 28, 2012, after 90 group members appeared in 90 different commercials aired in the [[Kant\u014d region|Kanto]], [[Kansai]] and [[T\u014dkai region|Tokai]] regions of Japan.<ref name=\"yahoosg20120307\">{{cite web|url=http://sg.news.yahoo.com/akb48s-guinness-world-record-064700948.html |title=AKB48's new Guinness World Record |publisher=Yahoo! Singapore|work=Cinema Online|date=March 7, 2012|accessdate=May 10, 2012}}</ref> Japanese ambassador to the United States [[Ichir\u014d Fujisaki]], on meeting the group during its visit to Washington, D.C., said that \"AKB\" stood for \"adorable, kind and beautiful\".<ref name=\"washingtonpost20120327\"/> On February 1, 2012, [[Japan Post]] issued a stamp commemorating the group.<ref name=\"thejapantimes20111125\">{{cite web|url=http://www.japantimes.co.jp/text/nn20111125f3.html |title=New postage stamp sheets feature AKB48 |publisher=Yahoo! Singapore|work=Japan Times |date=November 25, 2011|accessdate=May 10, 2012}}</ref>\n\n==Controversies==\nOne of the group's risqu\u00e9 music videos have also been considered controversial. \"[[Heavy Rotation (song)|Heavy Rotation]]\"'s video was criticized by Western reporters for showing AKB48 members in lingerie, hugging,<ref name=\"yahoonews20120420\">{{cite web|url=https://www.google.com/hostednews/afp/article/ALeqM5gf10h58-VhSyDji_3A4qRdKzyBxQ?docId=CNG.18634ec517d1075c5bd67dd43cff9063.921|title=Japan all-girl group ad 'encourages homosexuality'|work=[[Agence France-Presse]]|date=April 20, 2012|accessdate=April 12, 2013}}</ref> kissing and sharing a bath. Its director, [[Mika Ninagawa]], said that she wanted to appeal to men and women with a creative, fun video because of the group's increasing popularity among girls.<ref>{{cite journal|title=\u30b9\u30da\u30b7\u30e3\u30eb\u30ed\u30f3\u30b0\u30a4\u30f3\u30bf\u30d3\u30e5\u30fc: \u79cb\u5143\u5eb7\u300cAKB48\u306e\u79d8\u5bc6\u300d|journal=[[M girl]]|issue=2011 Spring/Summer|publisher=Matoi Publishing|isbn=9784905353027}}</ref> In an interview, she accepted responsibility for its content: \"Mr. Akimoto left everything to me. He did not give me any tips at all...I tried to show how AKB48 is in real life, in the video. In the dressing room, they seemed very close to each other. Then I came up with the concept [of a] girls' high school.\"<ref>{{cite web | url = http://nihongogo.com/2013/06/the-truth-behind-heavy-rotation/| title = The Truth Behind Heavy Rotation | first = Jeffrey | last = To | work = Nihongogo | date = June 23, 2013}}</ref>\n\nIn February 2013 group member [[Minami Minegishi]], had her head shaved and appeared in a YouTube video to apologize after it was reported by a tabloid that she had spent the night with a man in violation of her contract; she was demoted to the status of trainee. Although her shaved head was self-inflicted in an apologetic response to her fans and peers for her demotion, it was seen as an overreaction and attracted criticism of how the situation was handled.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2013/02/02/pop-star-shaves-head-minami-minegishi-japan_n_2608048.html |title=Minami Minegishi, Japanese Pop Star, Shaves Head As Penance For Dating |publisher=Huffington Post |date=February 2, 2013 |accessdate=April 2, 2013 |first=Dominique |last=Mosbergen}}</ref>\n\nA 2016 [[NHK]] documentary reported that the popularity of AKB48's handshake sessions may contribute to the decline of romantic relationships among young Japanese people, including \"[[herbivore men]]\", which triggered debates. According to the report, some fans would rather spend their time supporting their favourite idols than actively pursuing love interests.<ref>{{cite web|url = http://www.huffingtonpost.com/entry/japans-lack-of-romance-is_b_13927634.html|title = Japan\u2019s Lack of Romance: Is It Due to Idol Culture?|website=The Huffington Post|date = January 2, 2017|accessdate = January 2, 2017}}</ref>\n\n== Philanthropy ==\nOn April 1, 2011 the group released a digital charity single, \"Dareka no Tame ni (What Can I Do for Someone?)\", with its proceeds donated to [[2011 earthquake and tsunami|earthquake and tsunami relief]].<ref>{{cite web|title=AKB48\u3001\u30d5\u30a1\u30f3\u5f85\u671b\u306e\u540d\u66f2\u3092\u30c1\u30e3\u30ea\u30c6\u30a3\u30fc\u30bd\u30f3\u30b0\u3068\u3057\u3066\u914d\u4fe1|url=http://mdpr.jp/021135460|publisher=Model Press, Japan|accessdate=March 1, 2013|language=Japanese}}</ref> AKB48's 23rd single, \"[[Kaze wa Fuiteiru]]\", was dedicated to the disaster victims and also had lyrics of consolation.<ref>{{cite web|title=AKB48\u30012\u4f5c\u9023\u7d9a\"\u521d\u65e5\u30df\u30ea\u30aa\u30f3\"\u3000\u521d\u65e5\u58f2\u4e0a\u6b74\u4ee3\u6700\u9ad8\u306e104.6\u4e07\u679a|url=http://www.oricon.co.jp/news/rankmusic/2003129/full/?fb_ref=RightContents|publisher=Oricon|accessdate=March 1, 2013|language=Japanese}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=AKB48's Post-Quake Support Song Sells 1 Million on 1st Day|url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2011-10-26/akb48-post-quake-support-song-sells-1-million-on-1st-day|publisher=Anime News Network|accessdate=March 1, 2013}}</ref> In February 2012 AKB48 announced another \u00a5580&nbsp;million donation to the Japanese Red Cross, and it was reported that to date the group had raised a total of over \u00a51.25&nbsp;billion for earthquake and tsunami relief.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tokyograph.com/news/akb48-charity-efforts-have-raised-1-25-billion-yen-in-donations/|title=AKB48 charity efforts have raised 1.25 billion yen in donations|date=February 18, 2011|publisher=Tokyograph (based on articles by Oricon and Sankei sports)|accessdate=July 21, 2012}}</ref> On March 8, 2013 the group released \"Tenohira ga Kataru Koto\", another song dedicated to the March 2011 disaster victims, on its website for free digital download.<ref>{{cite web|author=|url=http://www.tokyohive.com/article/2013/02/akb48-to-distribute-another-charity-song-for-free/ |title=AKB48 to distribute another charity song for free |publisher=tokyohive.com |date=March 1, 2013 |accessdate=January 1, 2014}}</ref> On the second anniversary of the disaster AKB48 and its sister groups visited the affected areas, performing at schools and the AKB48, SKE48, NMB48 and HKT48 theaters with proceeds aiding the ongoing recovery.<ref>{{cite web|author=|url=http://www.tokyohive.com/article/2013/03/akb48-sister-groups-hold-special-performances-at-their-theaters-the-disaster-areas/ |title=AKB48 & sister groups hold special performances at their theaters + the disaster areas |publisher=tokyohive.com |date=March 11, 2013 |accessdate=January 1, 2014}}</ref>\n\n== Members ==\n{{main|List of AKB48 members|List of former members of AKB48}}\nAKB48's line up has frequently changed due to departures, admissions, team rotations, and transfers between AKB48 and its various sister groups.  {{As of|2019|10|30|df=US}}, the group consists of 108 members, divided among several teams: Team A with 22 members, Team K with 22 members, Team B with 23 members, and Team 4 with 27 members, Team 8 with 45 members, the last of which have 31 members serving concurrently with other AKB48 teams. There are Kenkyusei members, nine of whom serve on specific teams as understudies, and one of whom was recruited as a group of general understudies.<ref name=\"akb48members\">{{cite web|url=http://www.akb48.co.jp/about/members/|title=AKB48\u516c\u5f0f\u30b5\u30a4\u30c8\uff5c\u30e1\u30f3\u30d0\u30fc\u60c5\u5831 (AKB48 Official Site \u2013 Member List) |language=Japanese| work = AKB48 Official Website | accessdate = January 5, 2017|postscript=. List is subject to change from graduations and transfers.}}</ref><!-- member count: 22+22+23+27+45-31=108 --> Some members [[List of AKB48 members#Concurrent positions|belong concurrently]] to AKB48's sister groups,<ref name=\"akb48members\"/> and [[Mion Mukaichi]] is the general manager of AKB48 and its sister groups.\n\n== Discography ==\n{{main|AKB48 discography}}\n* ''[[Set List: Greatest Songs 2006\u20132007]]'' (2008)\n* ''[[Kamikyokutachi]]'' (2010)\n* ''[[Koko ni Ita Koto]]'' (2011)\n* ''[[1830m]]'' (2012)\n* ''[[Tsugi no Ashiato]]'' (2014)\n* ''[[Koko ga Rhodes da, Koko de Tobe!]]'' (2015)\n* ''[[0 to 1 no Aida]]'' (2015)\n* ''[[Thumbnail (album)|Thumbnail]]'' (2017)\n* ''[[Bokutachi wa, Ano Hi no Yoake o Shitteiru]]'' (2018)\n\n== Filmography ==\n{{main|AKB48 filmography}}\n\n== Awards and honors ==\nThe following table lists some of the major awards received by the group.\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Ceremony\n! Award\n! Nominated work\n! Result\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" |2009\n|[[51st Japan Record Awards]]\n|Special Award\n|\n|{{won}}\n|-\n|[[2009 Mnet Asian Music Awards|11th Mnet Asian Music Awards]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.mwave.me/en/mama/history/winners/list?years=2009|title=MAMA HISTORY - WINNERS 2009: The complete list {{!}} Mwave|website=www.mwave.me|language=en|access-date=2019-02-24}}</ref>\n|[[Mnet Asian Music Awards in the Special Awards Category|Asia Recommended Award (Japan)]]\n|\"[[River (AKB48 song)|River]]\"\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\" |2010\n|24th [[Japan Gold Disc Award]]\n|Special Award\n|\n|{{won}}\n|-\n|''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]] Japan'' Music Awards<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/photos/live/473172/chaka-khan-debbie-gibson-make-cameos-at-billboard-japan-awards|title=Chaka Khan, Debbie Gibson Make Cameos at Billboard Japan Awards|author= Rob Schwartz|work=Billboard|date=February 7, 2011|accessdate=January 28, 2014}}</ref>\n| Top Pop Artists\n|\n| {{won}}\n|-\n|GOOD DESIGN AWARD<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.g-mark.org/award/describe/37071?locale=en|title=Entertainment Project Design [AKB48]|website=Good Design Award|access-date=2019-02-24}}</ref>\n|Entertainment Project Design \n|\n|{{won}}\n|-\n| rowspan=\"6\"| 2011\n| [[Japan Gold Disc Award]]<ref>{{cite web |