ards]]\n| Gold Award\n|rowspan=\"2\"| \"[[Koi Suru Fortune Cookie]]\"\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| Grand Prix\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| rowspan=\"4\" |2014\n| [[56th Japan Record Awards]]\n| Grand Prix\n| \"[[Labrador Retriever (song)|Labrador Retriever]]\"\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| 28th [[Japan Gold Disc Award]]\n| Artist of the Year (Japan Domestic)\n|\n|{{won}}\n|-\n| 47th [[Japan Cable Awards]]\n| Cable Music Excellence [Outstanding Performance] Award\n| \"[[Kokoro no Placard]]\"\n| {{won}}\n|-\n|18th [[Space Shower Music Awards|space shower music video award]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.aoi-pro.com/news/award/20140310|title=\u300c\u7b2c18\u56deSPACE SHOWER MUSIC VIDEO AWARDS\u300d\u306b\u3066\u7279\u5225\u8cde\u307b\u304b\u53d7\u8cde!!|website=AOI Pro. Inc.|language=ja|access-date=2019-05-02}}</ref>\n|Special Award\n|\"Koi Suru Fortune Cookie\"\n|{{won}}\n|-\n|rowspan=7|2015\n| [[57th Japan Record Awards]]\n| Grand Prix\n| \"[[Bokutachi wa Tatakawanai]]\"\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| rowspan=2|29th [[Japan Gold Disc Award]]\n| Single of the year\n| \"[[Labrador Retriever (song)|Labrador Retriever]]\"\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| Album of the Year\n| \"[[Tsugi no Ashiato]]\"\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| 48th [[Japan Cable Awards]]\n| Cable Music Excellence [Outstanding Performance] Award\n| \"[[Kuchibiru ni Be My Baby]]\"\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| [[2015 Mnet Asian Music Awards|15th Mnet Asian Music Awards]]\n| Best Asian Artist Japan\n|\n| {{won}}\n|-\n|rowspan=2|[[The 3rd V Chart Awards]]\n|Favorite Artist Of The Year \n|\n|{{won}}\n|-\n|Top Group - Japan\n|\n|{{won}}\n|-\n| rowspan=\"7\" |2016\n| rowspan=\"2\" |''Billboard Japan'' Music Awards<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/7669062/billboard-japan-2016-artist-ranking-list-akb48|title=AKB48 Tops Billboard Japan's 2016 Artist Ranking: See the List|website=Billboard|access-date=2019-02-24}}</ref>\n|Artist of the year\n|\n|  {{won}}\n|-\n|Hot 100 of the Year\n|\"[[Tsubasa wa Iranai]]\"\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" |30th [[Japan Gold Disc Award]]\n|Single of the Year\n|\"[[Bokutachi wa Tatakawanai]]\"\n| {{won}}\n|-\n|Best 5 Albums\n|\"[[Koko ga Rhodes da, Koko de Tobe!]]\"\n\"[[0 to 1 no Aida]]\"\n |{{won}}\n|-\n|11th Taisho Ryou Music Award<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://info.kindenryu.co.jp/?eid=1329133|title=\u300c\u7b2c11\u56de\u5927\u6b63\u7434\u97f3\u697d\u5927\u8cde\u300d\u6388\u4e0e\u5f0f\u3092\u884c\u3044\u307e\u3057\u305f|website=\u7434\u4f1d\u6d41\u304b\u3089\u306e\u304a\u77e5\u3089\u305b {{!}} \u7434\u4f1d\u6d41\u5927\u6b63\u7434|language=ja|access-date=2019-05-02}}</ref>\n|Grand Prix\n|\"365 Nichi no Kamihikouki\"\n| {{won}}\n|-\n|88th Television Drama Academy Awards<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://thetv.jp/feature/drama-academy/88/awards/best-drama-song/|title=\u30c9\u30e9\u30de\u30bd\u30f3\u30b0\u8cde \u53d7\u8cde\u7d50\u679c 1\u4f4d\uff1a365\u65e5\u306e\u7d19\u98db\u884c\u6a5f\u3001AKB48 {{!}} \u7b2c88\u56de - \u30b6\u30c6\u30ec\u30d3\u30b8\u30e7\u30f3\u30c9\u30e9\u30de\u30a2\u30ab\u30c7\u30df\u30fc\u8cde|website=\u30b6\u30c6\u30ec\u30d3\u30b8\u30e7\u30f3|language=ja|access-date=2019-05-02}}</ref>\n|Best Theme Song Award\n|\"365 Nichi no Kamihikouki\"\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| 8th [[Dahsyatnya Awards]]\n| Best Guest Award ( Bintang Tamu Terdahsyat )\n|\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" |2017\n|31st [[Japan Gold Disc Award]]\n|Single of the Year\n|\"[[Tsubasa wa Iranai]]\"\n| {{won}}\n|-\n|[[2017 Mnet Asian Music Awards|19th Mnet Asian Music Awards]]\n| Best Asian Artist Japan\n|\n| {{won}}\n|-\n|2018\n|32nd Japan Gold Disc Award\n|Single of the Year\n|\"[[Negaigoto no Mochigusare]]\"\n|{{won}}\n|}\n\n=== {{anchor|Records attained}}Records set ===\nThe group and its songs have set the following records:\n* [[Guinness World Record]] for Largest Pop Group&nbsp;\u2014 In November 2010, Guinness named AKB48 the world's largest pop group.<ref name=\"guinnesslargestpopgroup\">{{cite web|url=http://www.guinnessworldrecords.com/records-8000/largest-pop-group/|title=Guinness Worlds Records&nbsp;\u2014 Largest pop group|publisher=Guinness World Records\n| accessdate=October 23, 2011}}</ref><ref name=\"yeinjee20101115\">{{cite web|url=http://yeinjee.com/2010/akb48-officially-world-biggest-group/|title=AKB48 is officially the world's biggest group|date=November 15, 2010|accessdate=June 29, 2011| archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20110718140453/http://yeinjee.com/2010/akb48-officially-world-biggest-group/| archivedate= July 18, 2011 |url-status = live}}</ref>\n* Guinness World Record for Most Number of Pop Singers Featured in a Video Game&nbsp;\u2014 In December 2012, the group's [[dating simulation game]] ''AKB1/149 Ren'ai S\u014dsenkyo'' featured 149 members.<ref name=\"sanspo20121207\"/>\n* Guinness World Record for Broadcasting the Most Same-Product Television Endorsements Within 24 Hours&nbsp;\u2014 In February 2012 AKB48 members appeared in 90 commercials for Asahi's Wonda Coffee Morning Shot, breaking the previous record of 60 commercials.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.tokyohive.com/article/2012/03/akb48-achieves-a-guinness-world-record-for-their-90-cms-for-wonda-coffee | title=AKB48 achieves a Guinness World Record for their 90 CMs for 'Wonda Coffee' | publisher=tokyohive | date=March 6, 2012 | accessdate=March 27, 2014}}</ref>\n* Most singles sold in Japan by a female artist&nbsp;\u2014 In May 2013, after the release of the group's 31st single (\"[[Sayonara Crawl]]\"), combined sales figures for AKB48 singles reached 21.852&nbsp;million since its 2006 debut in 2006 (breaking [[Ayumi Hamasaki]]'s previous record of 21.416&nbsp;million).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://ajw.asahi.com/article/cool_japan/culture/AJ201305280047 |title=AKB48 becomes best-selling singles female artist ever in Japan |publisher=Asahi Shimbun |date=May 22, 2013 |accessdate=March 15, 2014 |url-status = dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130621063239/http://ajw.asahi.com/article/cool_japan/culture/AJ201305280047 |archivedate=June 21, 2013 }}</ref>\n* Highest Japanese sales of a female-group single&nbsp;\u2014 In June 2013 \"Sayonara Crawl\"'s sales reached 1,872,000 copies, breaking [[Speed (Japanese band)|Speed's]] 1997 record for \"White Love\".<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.tokyohive.com/article/2013/06/akb48s-latest-single-is-the-best-selling-single-for-a-female-group | title=AKB48's latest single is the best selling single for a female group | publisher=tokyohive | date=June 7, 2013 | accessdate=March 27, 2014}}</ref> The single's total sales reached 1,955,800.<ref name=\"www22.atwiki.jp\">{{cite web|url=http://www22.atwiki.jp/akb48uriage/pages/233.html |title=AKB48 \u58f2\u4e0a \u2013 \u3055\u3088\u306a\u3089\u30af\u30ed\u30fc\u30eb |accessdate=March 13, 2014 |url-status = dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140312224650/http://www22.atwiki.jp/akb48uriage/pages/233.html |archivedate=March 12, 2014 }}</ref>\n* Most consecutive million-selling singles sold in Japan&nbsp;\u2014 In October 2013 AKB48's 33rd single (\"[[Heart Electric]]\") sold 1,021,000 copies on its first day, becoming the group's 14th consecutive million-selling single and breaking the previous record of 13 held by [[B'z]].<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.tokyohive.com/article/2013/10/akb48s-latest-single-heart-ereki-sold-over-a-million-copies-in-one-day | title=AKB48's latest single 'Heart Ereki' sells over a million copies in one day | publisher=tokyohive | date=October 30, 2013 | accessdate=March 27, 2014}}</ref>\n* Most million-selling singles in Japan&nbsp;\u2014 In December 2013, the group's 34th single (\"[[Suzukake no Ki no Michi de \"Kimi no Hohoemi o Yume ni Miru\" to Itte Shimattara Bokutachi no Kankei wa D\u014d Kawatte Shimau no ka, Bokunari ni Nan-nichi ka Kangaeta Ue de no Yaya Kihazukashii Ketsuron no Y\u014d na Mono]]\") sold 1,033,000 copies during its first week. AKB48's 16th million-selling single, it broke the previous record held by B'z for 13 years and nine months.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.tokyohive.com/article/2013/12/akb48-score-their-16th-million-selling-single | title=AKB48 score their 16th million-selling single | publisher=tokyohive | date=December 16, 2013 | accessdate=March 27, 2014}}</ref>\n* Highest Japanese sales of a female single&nbsp;\u2014 In June 2017, the group's 48th single (\"[[Negaigoto no Mochigusare]]\") sold 2,555,912 copies during its first week. It broke the previous record held by Dreams Come True.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.billboard-japan.com/d_news/detail/51793/2 | title=\u3010\u30d3\u30eb\u30dc\u30fc\u30c9\u3011AKB48\u300e\u9858\u3044\u3054\u3068\u306e\u6301\u3061\u8150\u308c\u300f\u304c250\u4e07\u679a\u7a81\u7834\u3001\u30b7\u30f3\u30b0\u30eb\u30fb\u30bb\u30fc\u30eb\u30b9\u30fb\u30c1\u30e3\u30fc\u30c8\u9996\u4f4d\u7372\u5f97 | publisher=Billboard JAPAN | date=June 5, 2017 | accessdate=June 5, 2017}}</ref>\n\n== Sister groups ==\n{{main|AKB48 Group}}\n\nAKB48 has sister groups created domestically and overseas, which are collectively referred to as [[AKB48 Group]].\n\n== See also ==\n*[[Oricon]]\n*[[Count Down TV]]\n*[[Japan Record Awards]]\n*[[Billboard Japan Music Awards]]\n*[[K\u014dhaku Uta Gassen]]\n\n== Notes ==\n{{reflist|group=\"note\"}}\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n<!-- Per [[WP:ELMINOFFICIAL]], choose one official website only -->\n{{Commons category|AKB48}}\n* {{Official website|https://www.akb48.co.jp}} {{in lang|ja}}\n\n\n{{AKB48}}\n{{AKB48 singles}}\n{{Japan Gold Disc Award for Artist of the Year}}\n{{Mnet Asian Music Award for Best Asian Artist}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Akb48}}\n[[Category:Official website different in Wikidata and Wikipedia]]\n[[Category:AKB48| ]]\n[[Category:Korean-language singers of Japan]]\n[[Category:Japanese idol groups]]\n[[Category:Japanese girl groups]]\n[[Category:Musical groups established in 2005]]\n[[Category:2005 establishments in Japan]]\n[[Category:Musical groups from Akihabara]]\n[[Category:Defstar Records artists]]\n[[Category:King Records (Japan) artists]]\n